const STOCK_DESCRIPTIONS_DATA = {"AAPL": "Apple Inc. designs, manufactures, and markets consumer electronics, computer software, and online services. The company's key products include iPhones, Mac computers, iPads, Apple Watches, and AirPods, as well as its ecosystem of software and services, including the App Store, Apple Music, and iCloud. As a leading innovator in the technology industry, Apple plays a significant role in shaping the global digital landscape.", "MSFT": "Microsoft is a multinational technology company that develops, manufactures, licenses, and supports a wide range of software products, services, and devices. The company's key products and services include the Windows operating system, Office productivity software, Azure cloud computing platform, and Xbox gaming console. As one of the world's largest and most influential technology companies, Microsoft plays a significant role in shaping the digital landscape and driving innovation in various industries.", "NVDA": "NVIDIA Corporation is a technology company that designs, manufactures, and markets graphics processing units (GPUs) and high-performance computing hardware. The company's products and services include its GeForce gaming GPUs, Quadro professional GPUs, Tesla datacenter GPUs, and Deep Learning SDKs, which power artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML) applications. NVIDIA's innovative technologies enable a wide range of industries, including gaming, professional visualization, datacenter computing, and autonomous vehicles.", "AMZN": "Amazon is a multinational e-commerce company that operates as a consumer technology and e-commerce platform, offering a wide range of products and services, including online retail, cloud computing, advertising, and artificial intelligence. The company's key products and services include its e-commerce platform, Amazon Web Services (AWS), and its digital media offerings, such as Prime Video and Amazon Music. As a leading player in the digital economy, Amazon matters for its significant impact on the retail landscape, its innovative approach to technology, and its influence on consumer behavior.", "GOOGL": "Alphabet Inc. is a multinational conglomerate specializing in Internet-related services and products. The company's key products and services include Google search, advertising, cloud computing through Google Cloud Platform, and hardware products such as Pixel smartphones and Google Home smart speakers. As a leader in the digital landscape, Alphabet plays a significant role in shaping the way people access information, communicate, and conduct business online.", "META": "Meta Platforms, Inc. operates as a technology company, providing products and services to facilitate communication, online interaction, and access to information. Its key products and services include Facebook, Instagram, and WhatsApp, as well as the Oculus virtual reality platform and the Meta Quest virtual reality headset. As a leading player in the digital landscape, Meta Platforms plays a significant role in shaping online experiences and influencing global communication trends.", "BRK.B": "Berkshire Hathaway is a multinational conglomerate holding company that engages in a wide range of businesses, including insurance, retail, manufacturing, and services. The company operates through several key subsidiaries, including GEICO, BNSF Railway, and Berkshire Hathaway Energy, among others. As a diversified conglomerate with a market value of over $600 billion, Berkshire Hathaway is one of the largest and most successful companies in the world.", "AVGO": "Broadcom Inc is a technology company that designs, develops, and supplies a range of semiconductor and infrastructure software solutions, including Wi-Fi and Bluetooth connectivity, storage, networking, and software management products. The company's products are used in various industries, including data center, enterprise, and mobile devices, enabling faster, more secure, and efficient data transfer and processing. As a leading provider of connectivity and infrastructure solutions, Broadcom plays a critical role in driving the development of modern technologies and transforming the way people live and work.", "TSLA": "Tesla, Inc. is a leading electric vehicle (EV) and clean energy company that designs, manufactures, and sells EVs, solar panels, and energy storage products. The company's key products include the Model S, Model 3, Model X, Model Y, and Cybertruck, as well as its solar panels and Powerwall energy storage systems. As a pioneer in the EV industry, Tesla matters for its role in accelerating the global transition to sustainable energy and its influence on the automotive and renewable energy sectors.", "LLY": "Eli Lilly and Company is a multinational pharmaceutical corporation that develops, manufactures, and markets human pharmaceuticals and animal health products. The company's key products include diabetes treatments such as Humalog and Trulicity, cancer medications like Alimta and Cyramza, and mental health treatments like Prozac and Cymbalta. As a leading developer of innovative treatments, Eli Lilly plays a significant role in improving patient outcomes and advancing healthcare globally.", "WMT": "Walmart operates as a multinational retail corporation that offers a wide range of products and services, including groceries, general merchandise, and services such as pharmacy and vision centers. The company operates through various formats, including Walmart U.S., Walmart International, and Sam's Club, and is one of the world's largest retailers by revenue. As a low-cost leader, Walmart provides affordable shopping options to millions of customers worldwide.", "JPM": "JPMorgan Chase is a multinational investment bank and financial services company that provides a range of products and services including consumer and commercial banking, investment banking, and asset management. The company offers a variety of financial products and services to individuals, businesses, governments, and institutions, including checking and savings accounts, credit cards, home loans, and investment advice. As one of the largest and most influential financial institutions in the world, JPMorgan Chase plays a significant role in facilitating global economic activity and providing financial stability.", "V": "Visa Inc. is a payments technology company that facilitates electronic transactions between merchants, financial institutions, and consumers worldwide. The company's key products and services include payment processing, digital wallets, and card issuance, enabling secure and convenient transactions across various channels. As a leading global payments network, Visa plays a critical role in the digital economy, connecting billions of people and businesses worldwide.", "MA": "Mastercard Incorporated is a technology company that provides transaction processing and payment solutions to consumers, merchants, financial institutions, and governments worldwide. The company's key products and services include payment processing, digital payments, and data analytics, facilitating secure and convenient transactions across various channels. As a leading global payments technology company, Mastercard plays a critical role in shaping the future of commerce and enabling seamless financial transactions.", "UNH": "UnitedHealth Group is a diversified healthcare company that provides health insurance coverage and health and wellness services to individuals, employers, and governments worldwide. The company offers a range of products and services, including UnitedHealthcare insurance plans, Optum health services, and IngenioRx pharmacy benefit management. As one of the largest health insurers in the US, UnitedHealth Group plays a significant role in shaping the country's healthcare landscape and improving access to quality care.", "COST": "Costco Wholesale is a multinational American multinational retailer that operates a chain of membership-based warehouse clubs offering a wide selection of products, including fresh produce, meats, dairy products, electronics, clothing, and home goods. The company provides a one-stop shopping experience for its members, offering competitive prices on a vast array of products and services. As one of the world's largest retailers, Costco plays a significant role in the global consumer staples market, serving millions of members worldwide.", "NFLX": "Netflix is a global streaming service provider that offers a wide range of TV shows, movies, and documentaries to its subscribers. The company's key products include its flagship streaming service, which offers both ad-supported and ad-free plans, as well as its DVD rental service, which allows customers to rent DVDs by mail. As a leading player in the streaming industry, Netflix has disrupted traditional television and film distribution models, providing users with on-demand access to a vast library of content.", "PG": "Procter & Gamble is a multinational consumer goods corporation that develops and markets a diverse portfolio of consumer staples products, including household care, beauty, and personal care items such as Tide laundry detergent, Gillette razors, and Pantene hair care products. The company operates globally, serving over 5 billion consumers in nearly 180 countries. As a leader in the consumer staples sector, Procter & Gamble's products are staples in many households worldwide, providing essential goods and services to consumers.", "JNJ": "Johnson & Johnson is a multinational healthcare company that develops, manufactures, and markets a diverse range of pharmaceutical, medical device, and consumer goods products. Its key offerings include prescription medications, medical devices, and consumer products such as baby care and oral care products. As a leading healthcare company, Johnson & Johnson plays a significant role in improving human health and well-being worldwide.", "HD": "Home Depot is a leading home improvement retailer that offers a wide range of products and services for building, renovating, and maintaining homes and commercial properties. The company's product offerings include lumber, building materials, tools, and home decor items, as well as services such as installation and repair. As a major player in the home improvement industry, Home Depot provides essential products and services to homeowners, professionals, and commercial customers, driving growth and stability in the US economy.", "ABBV": "AbbVie is a global biopharmaceutical company that develops and markets a range of pharmaceutical products, including immunology, oncology, and virology treatments, such as Humira, Skyrizi, and Venclexta. The company's portfolio also includes AndroGel, a testosterone replacement therapy, and Imbruvica, a treatment for certain types of blood cancer. As a leading player in the pharmaceutical industry, AbbVie plays a significant role in addressing various health needs and improving patient outcomes.", "CRM": "Salesforce is a cloud-based software company that provides customer relationship management (CRM) solutions to businesses of all sizes. Its key products and services include the Salesforce Customer 360 platform, which offers a suite of cloud-based applications for sales, marketing, customer service, and more, as well as its Einstein AI technology. As a leader in the CRM market, Salesforce helps businesses connect with their customers and drive growth through data-driven insights and personalized experiences.", "XOM": "Exxon Mobil is a multinational energy corporation that explores, produces, and refines oil and natural gas, as well as manufactures and markets petroleum products, including gasoline, diesel fuel, and jet fuel. The company operates in over 50 countries and is a leading producer of oil and natural gas, with a significant presence in the refining and petrochemicals sectors. As one of the largest publicly traded oil and gas companies in the world, Exxon Mobil plays a critical role in meeting global energy demand and shaping the future of the energy industry.", "ADBE": "Adobe is a multinational software company that provides a range of software solutions for creative professionals, businesses, and enterprises. Its key products and services include Creative Cloud, a suite of creative apps such as Photoshop and Illustrator, as well as Experience Cloud, a platform for customer experience management and digital marketing. As a leader in the digital experience management space, Adobe enables businesses to create, manage, and deliver engaging experiences across various channels and devices.", "AMD": "Advanced Micro Devices (AMD) is a leading semiconductor company that designs, manufactures, and markets microprocessors, graphics processing units (GPUs), and other computer hardware solutions for the gaming, professional visualization, datacenter, and consumer electronics markets. The company's products are used in a wide range of applications, including personal computers, servers, gaming consoles, and mobile devices. As a key competitor to Intel, AMD plays a significant role in shaping the global technology landscape and driving innovation in the semiconductor industry.", "KO": "Coca-Cola Company is a multinational beverage corporation that manufactures, markets, and distributes a portfolio of non-alcoholic beverage brands, including Coca-Cola, Fanta, Sprite, and Minute Maid, among others. The company operates in over 200 countries and is one of the largest beverage companies in the world, with a diverse range of products that cater to various tastes and preferences. As a leading consumer staples company, Coca-Cola plays a significant role in the global beverage industry, providing a consistent source of revenue and employment for millions of people worldwide.", "CVX": "Chevron is a multinational energy corporation that explores, produces, and transports crude oil and natural gas, as well as refines and markets petroleum products. The company's key products include gasoline, diesel fuel, jet fuel, lubricants, and other petrochemicals. As one of the world's largest energy companies, Chevron plays a significant role in meeting global energy demands while investing in cleaner energy solutions.", "MRK": "Merck is a global healthcare company that discovers, develops, manufactures, and distributes a range of pharmaceuticals, vaccines, and animal health products. The company's key products include Gardasil (human papillomavirus vaccine), Keytruda (immunotherapy treatment for various cancers), and Januvia (diabetes medication). As a leading developer of innovative treatments, Merck plays a significant role in advancing global health and improving patient outcomes.", "CSCO": "Cisco Systems, Inc. is a technology company that designs, manufactures, and sells networking hardware, software, and telecommunications equipment. The company's key products and services include routers, switches, network security systems, and collaboration tools, which enable businesses and organizations to connect, communicate, and operate more efficiently. As a leading provider of networking solutions, Cisco plays a critical role in facilitating global communication and digital transformation.", "PEP": "PepsiCo is a multinational food and beverage corporation that manufactures, markets, and distributes a diverse portfolio of consumer products, including carbonated soft drinks, juices, waters, snacks, and other food items. The company's key brands include Pepsi, Gatorade, Tropicana, Lay's, Doritos, and Cheetos, among others. As one of the largest food and beverage companies globally, PepsiCo plays a significant role in shaping the consumer packaged goods industry.", "TMO": "Thermo Fisher Scientific is a leading life sciences company that develops, manufactures, and markets a wide range of products and services for research, analysis, and diagnostics. Its key offerings include laboratory equipment, reagents, and software for genomics, proteomics, and other life sciences applications, as well as pharmaceutical and biotechnology manufacturing equipment. As a global leader in its industry, Thermo Fisher plays a critical role in advancing scientific research and improving healthcare outcomes.", "ACN": "Accenture is a global professional services company that provides a range of services including consulting, technology, and outsourcing to clients across various industries. The company's services include digital transformation, cloud, cybersecurity, and artificial intelligence, among others. As a leading technology consulting firm, Accenture helps organizations navigate complex business challenges and stay ahead in a rapidly changing digital landscape.", "MCD": "McDonald's is a fast-food giant that operates a global chain of restaurants serving a variety of burgers, fries, chicken nuggets, salads, and breakfast items. The company's iconic brand is recognized for its convenience, affordability, and quick service, making it a staple in the fast-food industry. As one of the world's largest restaurant chains, McDonald's matters to consumers and investors alike due to its widespread presence and influence on the global food market.", "DIS": "The Walt Disney Company is a global entertainment and media conglomerate that operates through various segments, including media networks, parks and resorts, and studio entertainment. The company's key products and services include film and television production, cable and broadcast television networks, and theme park resorts such as Disneyland and Walt Disney World. As a leader in the entertainment industry, Disney plays a significant role in shaping popular culture and providing family-friendly content to audiences worldwide.", "TXN": "Texas Instruments designs, manufactures, and sells semiconductors and other electronic components, including analog and embedded processing products, as well as wireless connectivity and automation solutions. The company's products are used in a wide range of applications, including industrial automation, automotive systems, medical devices, and consumer electronics. As a leading provider of semiconductor technology, Texas Instruments plays a critical role in enabling innovation and driving growth in the global electronics industry.", "INTC": "Intel Corporation is a technology company that designs, manufactures, and sells semiconductor chips and related products, including microprocessors, chipsets, and other interconnect products. The company's products are used in a wide range of applications, including personal computers, data centers, artificial intelligence, and the Internet of Things (IoT). As a leader in the semiconductor industry, Intel plays a critical role in enabling the development of innovative technologies and driving the growth of the global digital economy.", "BA": "Boeing is a multinational aerospace and defense corporation that designs, manufactures, and sells commercial airplanes, defense, space, and security systems worldwide. The company's key products include commercial jetliners, military aircraft, satellites, and space exploration systems, serving a diverse customer base across industries. As a leading player in the global aerospace industry, Boeing plays a critical role in shaping the future of transportation, defense, and space exploration.", "NKE": "Nike, Inc. is a multinational consumer goods company that designs, develops, and sells athletic footwear, apparel, and equipment. The company's portfolio includes a range of products, including running shoes, basketball sneakers, and sportswear, as well as its popular Jordan and Converse brands. As a leading global sportswear brand, Nike matters for its significant influence on the athletic apparel market and its commitment to innovation, sustainability, and social responsibility.", "GS": "Goldman Sachs is a multinational investment bank and financial services company that provides a range of products and services to corporations, financial institutions, governments, and high-net-worth individuals. The company's key offerings include investment banking, securities trading, asset management, and consumer and commercial banking. As one of the world's largest and most influential financial institutions, Goldman Sachs plays a significant role in facilitating global economic transactions and shaping market trends.", "CAT": "Caterpillar Inc is a leading manufacturer of heavy machinery and equipment, including earthmoving, mining, and construction equipment, as well as diesel and natural gas engines. The company's product portfolio includes wheel loaders, excavators, and motor graders, among others, which are used in various industries such as construction, mining, and energy. Caterpillar plays a significant role in global infrastructure development and is a key player in the industrials sector.", "MS": "Morgan Stanley is a multinational investment bank and financial services company that provides a range of products and services including investment banking, securities, investment management, and wealth management. The company's key offerings include brokerage services, investment research, and asset management solutions for institutional and individual clients. As one of the largest financial institutions globally, Morgan Stanley plays a significant role in facilitating capital markets and advising clients on strategic financial decisions.", "PLTR": "Palantir Technologies is a software company that develops and sells data integration and analytics platforms to commercial and government clients. Its key products include Palantir Gotham, a data integration platform, and Palantir Foundry, a cloud-based data management platform. By providing advanced data management and analytics capabilities, Palantir helps organizations make data-driven decisions and gain insights from complex data sets.", "NOW": "ServiceNow is a cloud-based software company that provides digital workflows for enterprise organizations, helping them automate and manage various business processes. The company's key products and services include the Now Platform, which offers IT service management, customer service management, and security incident response, among other capabilities. By streamlining operations and improving efficiency, ServiceNow enables businesses to enhance customer experiences and drive growth.", "BAC": "Bank of America is a multinational banking and financial services corporation that provides a range of financial products and services to individuals, businesses, and institutions. The company's key products and services include consumer and commercial banking, wealth management, and investment banking, as well as credit cards, loans, and other financial solutions. As one of the largest banks in the US, Bank of America plays a significant role in the country's financial system and economy.", "AMGN": "Amgen is a biotechnology company that discovers, develops, manufactures, and delivers innovative human therapeutics. The company's key products include Enbrel (etanercept) for rheumatoid arthritis and psoriasis, Neulasta (pegfilgrastim) for neutropenia, and Repatha (evolocumab) for hypercholesterolemia. As a leader in the biotechnology industry, Amgen's treatments improve the lives of millions of patients worldwide.", "GE": "General Electric is a multinational conglomerate that operates in the fields of aviation, healthcare, energy, and industry, providing a range of products and services including jet engines, medical imaging equipment, and power generation equipment. The company's diverse portfolio enables it to serve a broad customer base across various industries, from aerospace and healthcare to energy and transportation. As a leading industrial company, General Electric plays a significant role in shaping the global economy through its innovative technologies and solutions.", "LOW": "Lowe's Companies, Inc. operates as a home improvement retailer, offering a wide range of products and services for the repair, maintenance, and improvement of homes and buildings. The company's product offerings include lumber and building materials, appliances, tools, and home decor items, as well as services such as installation and maintenance. As a leading player in the home improvement market, Lowe's provides essential products and services to homeowners and professionals, driving growth in the U.S. housing market.", "UBER": "Uber Technologies, Inc. is a technology company that provides ride-hailing, food delivery, and other mobility services through its platform. The company's key products and services include Uber Ride, Uber Eats, Uber Freight, and Uber Movement, among others. As a leading player in the gig economy, Uber has transformed the way people and goods move, making it easier and more convenient to get around cities worldwide.", "BKNG": "Booking Holdings is a leading digital travel company that operates several well-known online travel agencies, including Booking.com, Priceline.com, Agoda.com, and Kayak.com. These platforms provide users with access to a vast inventory of travel products, including accommodations, flights, car rentals, and package deals. By connecting travelers with a wide range of options, Booking Holdings facilitates the booking process and drives growth in the global travel industry.", "SBUX": "Starbucks Corporation is a global coffee company that operates a chain of coffee shops, offering a range of specialty coffee beverages, teas, and other food and beverage items. The company's key products and services include its signature coffee drinks, as well as a selection of food items, including pastries, sandwiches, and salads. As a leading player in the coffee and retail industry, Starbucks matters to consumers and investors alike, with a strong brand presence and significant market share.", "TMUS": "T-Mobile US, Inc. is a wireless communications provider that offers a range of mobile services, including postpaid and prepaid wireless voice, data, and text services. The company's key products and services include its Magenta and Magenta Plus plans, as well as its Home Internet and TV services. As a leading player in the US wireless market, T-Mobile matters for its impact on the telecommunications industry and its influence on consumer mobility and connectivity options.", "WFC": "Wells Fargo is a multinational financial services company providing banking, investment, mortgage, and consumer finance products to individuals, businesses, and institutions. The company offers a range of services, including checking and savings accounts, credit cards, home loans, and investment management. As one of the largest banks in the US, Wells Fargo plays a significant role in the country's financial system, serving over 70 million customers worldwide.", "T": "AT&T Inc. is a multinational conglomerate providing a range of communication, media, and technology services to consumers and businesses worldwide. The company offers a diverse portfolio of products and services, including wireless voice and data services, video and broadband services, and advertising and sponsorship services through its WarnerMedia subsidiary. As one of the largest telecommunications companies globally, AT&T plays a significant role in shaping the digital landscape and connecting people, businesses, and communities.", "PFE": "Pfizer is a multinational pharmaceutical corporation that develops, manufactures, and distributes a wide range of prescription medicines, vaccines, and consumer healthcare products. The company's portfolio includes key products such as vaccines for COVID-19, pneumococcal disease, and influenza, as well as medications for conditions like hypertension, diabetes, and cancer. As one of the world's largest pharmaceutical companies, Pfizer plays a significant role in improving global health outcomes and advancing medical innovation.", "IBM": "IBM is a technology company that provides a range of technology products and services, including cloud computing, artificial intelligence, blockchain, and consulting services. The company's key products and services include Watson, a cloud-based AI platform, and Red Hat, a leading open-source software company acquired in 2019. As one of the world's largest and most influential technology companies, IBM plays a significant role in shaping the future of technology and driving innovation across industries.", "ORCL": "Oracle Corporation is a multinational technology company that provides enterprise software solutions, including database management, cloud computing, and enterprise resource planning. The company's key products and services include the Oracle Database, Oracle Cloud Infrastructure, and Oracle Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) and Human Capital Management (HCM) solutions. As a leader in the enterprise software market, Oracle helps businesses of all sizes manage their operations, make informed decisions, and drive growth.", "PM": "Philip Morris International Inc is a multinational tobacco company that manufactures and sells a range of tobacco products, including cigarettes, heated tobacco, and oral nicotine products. The company's portfolio includes well-known brands such as Marlboro, L&M, and Parliament, among others. As a leading player in the global tobacco industry, Philip Morris International plays a significant role in shaping the global tobacco landscape.", "DE": "Deere & Company is a leading manufacturer of agricultural, construction, and forestry equipment, as well as lawn and garden care products. The company's key products include tractors, combines, excavators, and lawn mowers, among others. As a global leader in the agricultural and construction equipment industries, Deere & Company plays a critical role in meeting the world's growing demand for food, infrastructure, and natural resources.", "UNP": "Union Pacific Corporation is a Class I freight railroad operating in the United States, providing rail transportation services to agricultural products, construction materials, consumer goods, and industrial products. The company's key products and services include rail transportation, intermodal transportation, and logistics solutions, connecting major West Coast and Gulf Coast ports to eastern and midwestern markets. As one of the largest railroads in North America, Union Pacific plays a critical role in the nation's supply chain, facilitating the movement of goods and supporting economic growth.", "AMAT": "Applied Materials is a leading provider of equipment, services, and software to the global semiconductor, display, and solar industries. The company's portfolio includes products for wafer fabrication, etching, deposition, and metrology, as well as services for manufacturing and research. By enabling the production of advanced technologies, Applied Materials plays a critical role in driving innovation and growth in key sectors.", "HON": "Honeywell International Inc. is a diversified multinational conglomerate that develops and manufactures a range of products and solutions for various industries, including aerospace, building technologies, and industrial automation. The company's key products and services include aircraft engines, industrial automation systems, security and surveillance equipment, and building management systems. As a leading provider of innovative technologies, Honeywell plays a critical role in shaping the future of industries and improving the efficiency and safety of operations worldwide.", "CMCSA": "Comcast Corporation is a global media, entertainment, and telecommunications company that provides a range of services, including cable television, high-speed internet, and wireless phone service through its Xfinity brand. The company also owns a significant stake in NBCUniversal, a leading media and entertainment company that operates a portfolio of television networks, film studios, and theme parks. As one of the largest media and telecommunications companies in the world, Comcast plays a critical role in shaping the modern media landscape and connecting millions of consumers to their favorite content and services.", "MMM": "3M is a multinational conglomerate that develops and manufactures a wide range of products, including adhesives, abrasives, laminates, ceramics, and other materials. The company's key products and services include Post-it Notes, Scotch tape, Thinsulate insulation, and various industrial and consumer goods. 3M's innovative products and technologies play a significant role in various industries, including healthcare, consumer goods, and industrial manufacturing.", "TGT": "Target Corporation is a multinational retailing company that operates a chain of general merchandise stores offering a wide range of products, including clothing, home goods, electronics, and groceries. The company's stores provide a one-stop shopping experience for customers, offering a variety of products from national and private-label brands. As one of the largest retailers in the United States, Target plays a significant role in shaping consumer spending habits and trends.", "CRWD": "CrowdStrike Holdings is a cloud-delivered endpoint security company that provides a range of cybersecurity solutions to protect against cyber threats. Its key products and services include the Falcon platform, which offers endpoint protection, threat intelligence, and incident response capabilities. By providing real-time threat detection and response, CrowdStrike helps organizations protect their networks, systems, and data from sophisticated cyber attacks.", "LMT": "Lockheed Martin is a leading global security and aerospace company that designs, develops, manufactures, and integrates advanced technology systems and products for defense, space, and civil government applications. The company's key products and services include fighter jets, helicopters, satellites, missile defense systems, and cybersecurity solutions. As a major player in the defense industry, Lockheed Martin plays a critical role in supporting national security and advancing technological innovation.", "PANW": "Palo Alto Networks is a cybersecurity company that provides network security systems to enterprises, governments, and service providers worldwide. The company's key products and services include its Next-Generation Firewall, Advanced Endpoint Protection, and Cloud Security offerings, which help protect against cyber threats and data breaches. By providing innovative security solutions, Palo Alto Networks helps organizations safeguard their digital assets and maintain the integrity of their networks.", "VZ": "Verizon Communications Inc is a leading provider of wireless and wireline communication services in the United States. The company offers a range of products and services, including wireless voice and data services, broadband internet, and television services, as well as cloud and security solutions. As one of the largest telecommunications companies in the US, Verizon plays a critical role in connecting people, businesses, and communities through its extensive network infrastructure.", "FDX": "FedEx Corporation is a multinational delivery services company that provides a range of services including express transportation, e-commerce solutions, and supply chain management. The company's key products and services include ground, express, and freight transportation, as well as logistics and e-commerce solutions. As a leading player in the logistics industry, FedEx plays a critical role in facilitating global trade and commerce, connecting businesses and individuals around the world.", "AXP": "American Express is a global financial services company that provides a range of products and services, including charge and credit cards, travel services, and merchant payment processing solutions. The company's key products include its popular consumer and business credit cards, as well as its travel rewards programs and loyalty initiatives. As a leading provider of payment and travel services, American Express plays a significant role in facilitating global commerce and consumer spending.", "MU": "Micron Technology is a leading global manufacturer of semiconductor devices, including DRAM, NAND flash memory, and other memory and storage solutions. The company's products are used in a wide range of applications, from consumer electronics and data centers to automotive and industrial systems. As a key supplier of memory and storage solutions, Micron Technology plays a critical role in enabling the development of emerging technologies such as artificial intelligence, the Internet of Things, and 5G networks.", "LRCX": "Lam Research Corporation is a technology company that designs, manufactures, and markets semiconductor processing equipment used in the production of integrated circuits and other semiconductor devices. The company's products include etch, deposition, and wafer cleaning equipment, as well as other related systems and services. By enabling the development of advanced semiconductor technologies, Lam Research plays a critical role in the global electronics industry, driving innovation and progress in fields such as computing, communications, and consumer electronics.", "INTU": "Intuit is a technology company that provides business and financial management solutions to individuals and small businesses. Its key products and services include TurboTax, QuickBooks, and Mint, which enable users to manage their finances, prepare taxes, and run their businesses. By simplifying financial tasks and providing personalized insights, Intuit helps its customers achieve financial stability and success.", "RTX": "Raytheon Technologies is a multinational conglomerate that designs, develops, and manufactures advanced aerospace and defense systems, including commercial and military aircraft, missiles, and cybersecurity solutions. The company's key products and services include the F-35 fighter jet, the Patriot missile defense system, and Pratt & Whitney commercial aircraft engines. As a leading player in the aerospace and defense industry, Raytheon Technologies plays a critical role in supporting national security, advancing technological innovation, and driving economic growth.", "SCHW": "Charles Schwab is a leading financial services company that provides brokerage, banking, and investment services to individuals and institutional clients. The company offers a range of products and services, including brokerage accounts, retirement accounts, investment advice, and banking services, through its online platform and network of retail branches. As one of the largest online brokerages, Schwab matters for its accessibility, low fees, and comprehensive investment solutions, making it a popular choice for individual investors and financial advisors.", "MRNA": "Moderna Therapeutics, operating under the ticker MRNA, is a biotechnology company focused on developing mRNA-based vaccines and therapeutics for infectious diseases, cancer, and rare genetic diseases. The company's pipeline includes its flagship COVID-19 vaccine, Spikevax, as well as candidates for influenza, HIV, and other conditions. By leveraging its innovative mRNA technology, Moderna aims to revolutionize the treatment and prevention of various diseases, transforming the future of medicine.", "SHOP": "Shopify is a Canadian e-commerce company that provides businesses with a platform to design, set up, and manage their online stores across various sales channels, including web, mobile, social media, online marketplaces, and physical retail locations. The company offers a suite of services, including payment processing, shipping and fulfillment, and customer engagement tools, to help merchants manage their online presence and grow their sales. As a leading e-commerce platform, Shopify enables businesses to reach a global customer base and compete in the rapidly evolving digital marketplace.", "COP": "ConocoPhillips is a multinational energy corporation that explores, produces, transports, and markets crude oil, natural gas, and natural gas liquids. The company operates in the upstream, midstream, and downstream segments of the energy industry, offering a range of products and services including refined products, lubricants, and petrochemicals. As one of the world's largest independent exploration and production companies, ConocoPhillips plays a significant role in meeting global energy demands.", "DHR": "Danaher Corporation is a global healthcare and industrial conglomerate that designs, manufactures, and markets a wide range of products and services. The company operates through three segments: Life Sciences, Diagnostics, and Environmental & Applied Solutions, offering products such as laboratory equipment, medical devices, and water quality testing solutions. As a leading player in the healthcare industry, Danaher's innovative solutions and technologies help improve patient care, advance scientific research, and protect public health.", "SO": "Southern Company is a leading energy provider that generates, transmits, and distributes electricity through its subsidiaries, including Alabama Power, Georgia Power, and Mississippi Power. The company's key products and services include electricity, natural gas, and other energy-related services, serving millions of customers across the southeastern United States. As a major player in the US energy sector, Southern Company plays a critical role in meeting the region's growing energy demands while promoting energy efficiency and sustainability.", "BLK": "Blackrock is a global investment management corporation that provides a range of investment and risk management solutions to institutional and retail clients. The company's key products and services include index funds, exchange-traded funds (ETFs), and actively managed investment portfolios. As one of the world's largest asset managers, Blackrock plays a significant role in shaping the global financial landscape and influencing investment trends.", "DUK": "Duke Energy is a multinational energy company that generates, transmits, and distributes electricity to approximately 7.7 million customers across the United States. The company operates a diverse portfolio of power plants, including natural gas, coal, and nuclear facilities, as well as renewable energy sources such as solar and wind power. As one of the largest electric utilities in the US, Duke Energy plays a critical role in providing reliable and affordable energy to its customers and supporting economic growth in the regions it serves.", "NEE": "NextEra Energy is a leading clean energy company that generates, transmits, and distributes electricity through its subsidiaries, including Florida Power & Light Company and Gulf Power Company, serving over 10 million customers. The company operates a diverse portfolio of renewable energy sources, including wind and solar power, and is one of the largest producers of wind and solar energy in the world. As a major player in the transition to a low-carbon economy, NextEra Energy plays a critical role in reducing greenhouse gas emissions and promoting sustainable energy solutions.", "PLD": "Prologis is a real estate investment trust (REIT) that specializes in the ownership, development, and management of logistics and distribution facilities globally. The company's portfolio includes a diverse range of properties, from traditional warehouses to more specialized facilities such as cold storage and e-commerce distribution centers. As a leading player in the logistics real estate sector, Prologis provides essential infrastructure for global supply chains, supporting the growth of e-commerce and other industries that rely on efficient and reliable distribution networks.", "AMT": "American Tower is a real estate investment trust that specializes in leasing space on communication towers, data centers, and other infrastructure to wireless carriers and broadcasters. The company's key products and services include tower leasing, data center leasing, and other communications infrastructure solutions. As a leading provider of wireless infrastructure, American Tower plays a critical role in supporting the growth and development of the global telecommunications industry.", "EL": "Estee Lauder Companies Inc is a multinational cosmetics and skincare company that develops, manufactures, and distributes a wide range of beauty and personal care products under various brand names, including Estee Lauder, MAC, Clinique, and La Mer. The company's portfolio includes skincare, makeup, fragrance, and hair care products, catering to diverse consumer needs and preferences. As a leading player in the global beauty industry, Estee Lauder Companies Inc drives innovation and growth through its commitment to quality, sustainability, and customer satisfaction.", "DG": "Dollar General operates a chain of variety retail stores offering a range of products, including groceries, household essentials, and general merchandise, primarily targeting price-conscious consumers in the United States. The company's stores are typically smaller than traditional retailers, allowing for lower prices and a convenient shopping experience. As a leading player in the discount retail space, Dollar General provides essential goods to underserved communities and competes with other discount retailers.", "NEM": "Newmont Corporation is a leading gold mining company that operates a portfolio of mines globally, producing gold, silver, copper, zinc, and other metals. The company's key products include gold, copper, and other precious and base metals, with a focus on delivering safe, responsible, and sustainable mining practices. As one of the world's largest gold producers, Newmont plays a significant role in meeting global demand for precious metals.", "FCX": "Freeport-McMoRan is a leading international mining company that engages in the exploration, mining, and production of copper, gold, molybdenum, silver, and other minerals. The company operates a diversified portfolio of assets globally, including the Grasberg mine in Indonesia, one of the world's largest copper and gold mines. As a major supplier of copper and other essential minerals, Freeport-McMoRan plays a critical role in supporting global economic growth and technological advancements.", "NUE": "Nucor is a leading steel producer and manufacturer of steel products, offering a diverse range of products including steel bars, steel plates, steel sheets, and steel tubing. The company operates a network of mills, recycling facilities, and distribution centers across the United States and Canada, providing a wide variety of steel products to the construction, automotive, and energy industries. As one of the largest steel producers in the United States, Nucor plays a critical role in meeting the country's growing demand for steel products.", "SLB": "SLB is a global energy services company that provides a range of products and services to the oil and natural gas industry, including drilling and completion, production, and project management solutions. The company's key products and services include drilling and completion fluids, cementing, and well intervention, as well as digital solutions for the energy industry. As a leading provider of energy services, SLB plays a critical role in helping to meet the world's increasing energy demands while also driving innovation and sustainability in the industry.", "EOG": "EOG Resources is a leading independent crude oil and natural gas company engaged in exploration, development, production, and marketing of hydrocarbon resources primarily in the United States, Canada, and the Permian Basin. The company's key products include crude oil, natural gas, and natural gas liquids, which are essential components of the global energy mix. As a major player in the energy sector, EOG Resources plays a critical role in meeting the world's increasing demand for energy while also driving innovation and sustainability in the industry.", "PXD": "Pioneer Natural Resources is an independent oil and gas exploration and production company that explores for, develops, and produces oil and natural gas in the United States and internationally. The company's key products include crude oil and natural gas, which it produces from its operations in the Permian Basin, Eagle Ford Shale, and other regions. As one of the largest independent oil and gas producers in the US, Pioneer Natural Resources plays a significant role in meeting the country's energy demands.", "SPG": "Simon Property Group is a real estate investment trust (REIT) that owns, develops, and manages a portfolio of retail and mixed-use properties across the United States and internationally. The company's properties feature a diverse range of key tenants, including department stores, specialty retailers, and dining and entertainment options. As one of the largest shopping mall operators in the world, Simon Property Group plays a significant role in shaping the retail landscape and driving economic growth in local communities.", "DLR": "Digital Realty is a global provider of cloud-connected data center, colocation, and interconnection solutions. The company offers a range of services and products, including data center space, cloud connectivity, and interconnection services, to support the growth of cloud computing and digital infrastructure. By providing secure, scalable, and interconnected data centers, Digital Realty enables businesses to efficiently deploy and manage their digital infrastructure.", "DOW": "Dow Inc is a multinational chemical company that develops and manufactures a range of products including plastics, chemicals, and agricultural sciences. The company's key products include plastics, coatings, and agricultural chemicals, which are used in various industries such as automotive, construction, and consumer goods. As a leading Materials company, Dow Inc plays a critical role in the global supply chain, providing essential materials and solutions that support economic growth and development.", "CF": "CF Industries Holdings, Inc. is a leading global fertilizer and industrial chemicals company that manufactures and distributes nitrogen-based products, including ammonia, urea, and diesel exhaust fluid. The company's products are used in agriculture, as well as in industrial applications such as fuel additives and pharmaceuticals. As a key supplier of nitrogen-based products, CF Industries plays a critical role in meeting the world's growing demand for food and other essential products.", "D": "Dominion Energy is a utility company that generates and distributes electricity and natural gas to approximately 7.5 million customers in 16 states. The company's key products and services include electricity and natural gas transmission, distribution, and sales, as well as regulated and non-regulated energy-related businesses. As a major energy provider in the United States, Dominion Energy plays a critical role in meeting the country's growing energy demands while also investing in renewable energy sources and grid modernization.", "AES": "AES Corp is a multinational energy company that generates and distributes electrical power to customers worldwide through a diverse portfolio of thermal and renewable energy sources. The company's key products and services include electricity generation, transmission, and distribution, as well as energy trading and marketing. As a leading player in the global energy sector, AES Corp plays a critical role in meeting the world's growing energy demands while promoting sustainable development and reducing carbon emissions.", "O": "Realty Income is a real estate investment trust (REIT) that owns and operates a diversified portfolio of commercial properties, including single-tenant retail, office, and industrial properties. The company generates revenue primarily through rent from its tenants, providing a stable source of income for investors. As one of the largest REITs in the world, Realty Income offers a unique investment opportunity for those seeking steady income and diversification in their portfolios.", "GOOG": "Alphabet Inc. is a multinational conglomerate that operates as a holding company for a portfolio of businesses, primarily focused on technology and innovation. Its key subsidiaries include Google, a leading internet search and online advertising platform, as well as other businesses such as Waymo, Verily, and Calico. As a leader in the digital landscape, Alphabet's innovative products and services have transformed the way people access information, communicate, and conduct business.", "GEV": "GE Vernova is a leading provider of power generation and grid solutions, delivering critical infrastructure to power the world's homes, businesses, and industries. The company's portfolio includes advanced gas turbines, steam turbines, and grid solutions that enable efficient and reliable energy transmission and distribution. As a key player in the global energy landscape, GE Vernova plays a vital role in supporting the transition to a cleaner, more sustainable energy future.", "LIN": "Linde plc is a multinational industrial gases company that provides a range of products and services, including atmospheric gases, process gases, and liquefied gases, to various industries such as healthcare, food and beverage, and energy. The company's key products include oxygen, nitrogen, argon, and carbon dioxide, as well as specialty gases and equipment for gas processing and handling. As a leading supplier of industrial gases, Linde plays a critical role in supporting the global economy and enabling the production of essential goods and services.", "ABT": "Abbott Laboratories is a diversified global healthcare company that develops, manufactures, and markets a range of products, including diagnostics, medical devices, nutritionals, and branded generic pharmaceuticals. The company's key products include its FreeStyle glucose monitoring systems, MitraClip transcatheter mitral valve repair system, and Similac infant formula. As a leading healthcare company, Abbott Laboratories plays a significant role in improving patient outcomes and enhancing quality of life through its innovative products and technologies.", "KLAC": "KLA Corporation is a leading global supplier of process control and yield management solutions for the semiconductor and data storage industries. The company's portfolio includes inspection and metrology systems, process control solutions, and yield management products that enable customers to improve manufacturing efficiency and product quality. By providing critical data and insights, KLA helps drive innovation and advancement in the fields of computing, communications, and data storage.", "C": "Citigroup, Inc. is a multinational investment bank and financial services corporation that provides a range of financial products and services to consumers, corporations, governments, and institutions. The company's key products and services include consumer banking, corporate and investment banking, markets and securities, and private banking. As one of the largest financial institutions globally, Citigroup plays a significant role in facilitating international trade, investment, and economic growth.", "GILD": "Gilead Sciences is a biopharmaceutical company that develops, manufactures, and commercializes therapies for the treatment of life-threatening infectious diseases, including HIV/AIDS, liver diseases, and cancer. The company's key products include Sovaldi, Harvoni, Epclusa, and Biktarvy, which are used to treat various viral infections and cancers. As a leader in the development of antiviral therapies, Gilead Sciences plays a significant role in improving patient outcomes and addressing some of the world's most pressing public health challenges.", "TJX": "TJX Companies operates as a multinational off-price department store chain, offering a wide range of products including apparel, home fashions, and accessories at discounted prices. The company's portfolio includes T.J. Maxx, Marshalls, and HomeGoods, among other brands, providing customers with a treasure hunt shopping experience. As a leading off-price retailer, TJX Companies offers a unique value proposition to consumers, driving growth and profitability in the retail industry.", "ISRG": "Intuitive Surgical designs, manufactures, and markets robotic-assisted surgical systems for various medical procedures, including urology, gynecology, and general surgery. The company's flagship product, the da Vinci Surgical System, enables surgeons to perform complex procedures with enhanced precision and minimally invasive techniques. By improving patient outcomes and reducing recovery times, Intuitive Surgical's technology has become a standard in modern surgical care.", "ADI": "Analog Devices is a global semiconductor company that designs, manufactures, and markets high-performance analog, mixed-signal, and digital signal processing integrated circuits for a wide range of applications, including industrial automation, automotive electronics, and consumer electronics. The company's products include data converters, amplifiers, and radio-frequency (RF) components, among others. Analog Devices plays a critical role in enabling the development of advanced technologies that drive innovation and growth in various industries.", "APH": "Amphenol is a leading global designer, manufacturer, and supplier of electrical, electronic and fiber-optic connectors, interconnect systems, antennas, sensors and sensor-based products, and coaxial and high-speed specialty cable. The company's products are used in a wide range of applications, including telecommunications, data communication, industrial, automotive, aerospace and defense, and consumer electronics. As a key supplier to the technology industry, Amphenol plays a critical role in enabling the growth and development of emerging technologies.", "ANET": "Arista Networks designs, manufactures, and sells cloud networking solutions that are used to build software-defined cloud networks. The company's products include Ethernet switches, routers, and software that enable customers to build and manage scalable, high-performance networks. Arista's solutions are used by cloud service providers, data centers, and enterprises to improve network efficiency, reduce costs, and enhance application performance.", "QCOM": "Qualcomm designs, manufactures, and markets semiconductor products and wireless communication technologies. The company's key products include mobile processors, modems, and Wi-Fi and Bluetooth chipsets, which are used in a wide range of devices, including smartphones, laptops, and automotive systems. As a leader in the development of 5G and other wireless technologies, Qualcomm plays a critical role in enabling the growth of mobile and connected devices.", "SYK": "Stryker Corporation is a leading medical technology company that develops, manufactures, and markets innovative medical devices and equipment for various medical specialties. The company's portfolio includes orthopedic implants, surgical instruments, and medical imaging systems, as well as spinal and trauma products. As a global healthcare leader, Stryker plays a critical role in improving patient outcomes and enhancing the quality of life for millions of people worldwide.", "WELL": "Welltower is a healthcare real estate investment trust (REIT) that invests in and manages a diversified portfolio of high-quality, healthcare-related properties, including medical offices, outpatient facilities, and senior housing communities. The company's properties are leased to a diverse group of healthcare providers, including physicians, hospitals, and healthcare systems, providing them with the space and infrastructure needed to deliver quality patient care. By investing in the healthcare real estate sector, Welltower aims to provide stable and growing income to its shareholders.", "ETN": "Eaton Corporation is a global diversified industrial manufacturer that provides solutions to help customers power, protect, and connect their equipment and vehicles. The company's key products and services include electrical systems, power management, hydraulics, and vehicle drivetrain and eMobility solutions. By enabling customers to improve efficiency, productivity, and safety, Eaton plays a critical role in various industries, including aerospace, automotive, and renewable energy.", "APP": "AppLovin is a leading mobile gaming and monetization company that provides a suite of solutions for developers and publishers to grow their mobile apps and games. Its key products and services include the AppLovin MAX platform, which offers a unified marketplace for mobile ad inventory, and the IronSource platform, which provides a range of monetization tools for mobile games. By helping developers and publishers succeed, AppLovin plays a critical role in the mobile gaming ecosystem and drives innovation in the industry.", "BX": "Blackstone Inc is a global investment management firm that provides alternative investment products and financial advisory services to institutional and individual clients. The company offers a range of products, including private equity, real estate, hedge funds, and credit funds, as well as wealth management and financial advisory services. As one of the largest alternative asset managers in the world, Blackstone plays a significant role in shaping the global financial landscape.", "CB": "Chubb Limited is a global insurance company that provides a range of property and casualty insurance products, including commercial and personal insurance, as well as reinsurance services. The company's key products and services include liability, property, workers' compensation, and specialty insurance, as well as risk management and insurance consulting services. As one of the world's largest publicly traded property and casualty insurers, Chubb Limited plays a significant role in helping businesses and individuals manage risk and recover from unexpected events.", "SPGI": "S&P Global is a leading provider of financial information and analytics, offering a range of products and services that help investors, corporations, and governments make informed decisions. The company's key offerings include S&P Dow Jones Indices, S&P Global Market Intelligence, and S&P Global Platts, which provide data, research, and ratings on stocks, bonds, and commodities. By providing critical insights and data, S&P Global helps drive transparency, efficiency, and innovation in the global financial markets.", "GLW": "Corning Inc. is a leading global technology company that specializes in the design, manufacture, and sale of glass, ceramics, and related materials for a range of applications, including telecommunications, consumer electronics, and life sciences. The company's key products include Gorilla Glass for smartphones and tablets, fiber optic cables, and display glass for TVs and monitors. As a key supplier to major technology companies, Corning plays a critical role in enabling the development and deployment of advanced technologies that transform the way people live and work.", "BMY": "Bristol Myers Squibb is a biopharmaceutical company that develops, manufactures, and markets prescription medicines for various diseases, including cancer, cardiovascular disease, and immunologic disorders. The company's key products include Opdivo, Revlimid, and Eliquis, which are used to treat a range of conditions, including lung cancer, multiple myeloma, and blood clots. As a leading player in the pharmaceutical industry, Bristol Myers Squibb plays a significant role in advancing medical research and improving patient outcomes.", "PH": "Parker Hannifin Corporation is a global diversified industrial company that designs, manufactures, and markets motion and control technologies and systems for various mobile, industrial, and aerospace markets. The company's key products and services include hydraulic, pneumatic, and electromechanical systems, as well as filtration and fluid power systems. As a leading provider of critical components and systems, Parker Hannifin plays a vital role in the development and operation of complex equipment and vehicles across various industries.", "MDT": "Medtronic is a global leader in medical technology, offering a wide range of products and therapies that treat various medical conditions, including cardiovascular, neurological, and spinal disorders. The company's key products include insulin pumps, pacemakers, and spinal implants, as well as surgical instruments and diagnostic equipment. As a pioneer in medical innovation, Medtronic plays a critical role in improving patient outcomes and enhancing the quality of life for millions of people worldwide.", "PGR": "Progressive Corporation is a leading provider of personal and commercial auto insurance, as well as other specialty property-casualty insurance products. The company offers a range of services, including auto insurance, home insurance, and motorcycle insurance, through its direct-to-consumer model and a network of independent agents. As one of the largest auto insurers in the US, Progressive plays a significant role in the country's insurance market.", "COF": "Capital One Financial Corporation is a diversified bank holding company that provides a range of financial products and services to consumers, small businesses, and commercial clients through its banking and credit card divisions. The company offers a variety of key products and services, including credit cards, auto loans, home equity loans, and banking services, as well as digital banking platforms and mobile payment solutions. As a leading player in the US banking industry, Capital One plays a significant role in facilitating consumer and commercial lending, driving economic growth, and shaping the future of financial services.", "IBKR": "Interactive Brokers Group is a leading online brokerage firm that provides a range of financial products and services, including brokerage, clearing, and execution services for stocks, options, futures, forex, and cryptocurrencies. The company offers a suite of trading platforms, including its flagship Trader Workstation, as well as mobile and web-based platforms, to support its clients' trading needs. As a low-cost provider with a global reach, Interactive Brokers matters to investors seeking efficient and cost-effective access to global markets.", "VRTX": "Vertex Pharmaceuticals is a biotechnology company that develops and commercializes innovative medicines for the treatment of serious and rare diseases, including cystic fibrosis and other genetic diseases. The company's key products include Kalydeco, Orkambi, and Trikafta, which are cystic fibrosis treatments, as well as its portfolio of other pipeline assets. Vertex's innovative therapies have transformed the treatment landscape for patients with rare and serious diseases, improving their quality of life and life expectancy.", "MCK": "McKesson Corporation is a healthcare services and information technology company that provides pharmaceutical and medical-surgical supply chain management solutions, as well as healthcare technology and analytics services. The company offers a range of products and services, including distribution of pharmaceuticals, vaccines, and medical supplies, as well as technology solutions for healthcare providers and payers. As a leading healthcare services company, McKesson plays a critical role in the delivery of patient care and the management of healthcare costs.", "CEG": "Constellation Energy is a leading competitive energy company that generates, trades, and supplies electricity, as well as provides energy management and risk management services to commercial and industrial customers. The company's key products and services include electricity generation, energy trading, and energy supply, as well as energy management and risk management solutions. As a major player in the competitive energy market, Constellation Energy plays a significant role in shaping the US energy landscape and providing essential services to its customers.", "HCA": "HCA Healthcare is a leading healthcare provider with a network of hospitals and healthcare facilities across the United States. The company offers a range of services, including acute care, outpatient services, and surgical care, through its 185 hospitals and more than 2,000 sites of care. As one of the largest private healthcare providers in the US, HCA plays a significant role in delivering high-quality patient care and advancing healthcare outcomes.", "CME": "CME Group is a global derivatives marketplace and clearinghouse that operates a range of financial exchanges, including the Chicago Mercantile Exchange, the Chicago Board of Trade, and the New York Mercantile Exchange. The company offers futures and options contracts on a variety of assets, including commodities, currencies, interest rates, and equity indexes, facilitating price discovery and risk management for market participants. As a leading provider of derivatives trading and clearing services, CME Group plays a critical role in global financial markets, enabling the efficient transfer of risk and facilitating the flow of capital.", "MO": "Altria Group, Inc. is a multinational consumer staples company that manufactures and sells tobacco products, including cigarettes, cigars, and smokeless tobacco. The company's portfolio includes iconic brands such as Marlboro, Virginia Slims, and Copenhagen, among others. As a leading player in the global tobacco industry, Altria's products and operations have a significant impact on the market and contribute to the company's position as a major player in the consumer staples sector.", "BSX": "Boston Scientific is a medical technology company that develops, manufactures, and markets medical devices used in various specialties, including cardiology, endoscopy, urology, and neuromodulation. The company's product portfolio includes interventional cardiology products, such as stents and catheters, as well as minimally invasive surgical devices and implantable neurostimulators. Boston Scientific's innovative medical technologies help improve patient outcomes and quality of life, making it a leading player in the global healthcare industry.", "NOC": "Northrop Grumman Corporation is a leading global aerospace and defense technology company that designs, develops, and manufactures innovative products and solutions for the U.S. military and other government agencies. The company's portfolio includes aircraft, space systems, cyber solutions, and logistics and modernization services, with key products such as the B-21 Raider stealth bomber and the LITENING advanced targeting pod. As a major player in the defense industry, Northrop Grumman plays a critical role in advancing national security and protecting global interests.", "HWM": "Howmet Aerospace is a leading global supplier of advanced aluminum and titanium aerostructures, engine components, and other highly engineered products for the aerospace and defense industries. The company's products serve major commercial and military aircraft manufacturers, including Boeing and Lockheed Martin, and are critical components in the production of commercial airliners and military fighter jets. As a key supplier to the aerospace industry, Howmet Aerospace plays a vital role in the development and production of advanced aircraft and defense systems.", "TT": "Trane Technologies is a global climate control company that designs, manufactures, and markets heating, ventilation, and air conditioning (HVAC) systems, as well as refrigeration and building services. The company's portfolio includes brands such as Trane, Thermo King, and American Standard, offering a range of products and solutions for residential, commercial, and industrial applications. As a leader in the HVAC industry, Trane Technologies plays a critical role in improving indoor air quality, energy efficiency, and sustainability for buildings and communities worldwide.", "CVS": "CVS Health is a diversified healthcare company that operates a chain of retail pharmacies, health insurance plans, and healthcare services. The company provides a range of products and services, including prescription medications, health insurance, pharmacy benefits management, and healthcare consulting. As one of the largest healthcare companies in the US, CVS Health plays a significant role in shaping the country's healthcare landscape and improving patient outcomes.", "DELL": "Dell Technologies is a multinational information technology company that designs, manufactures, and sells personal computers, servers, storage systems, and networking products. The company offers a wide range of products and services, including desktops, laptops, tablets, and data storage solutions, as well as cloud computing, cybersecurity, and artificial intelligence services. As a leading provider of end-to-end technology solutions, Dell Technologies plays a critical role in enabling businesses and organizations to operate efficiently and effectively in the digital age.", "GD": "General Dynamics is a leading aerospace and defense company that designs, builds, and delivers a wide range of products and services to the U.S. military, foreign governments, and commercial customers. Its key products and services include combat vehicles, ships, aircraft, and IT systems, as well as land and amphibious systems, and mission-critical communications and information technology solutions. As a major player in the defense industry, General Dynamics plays a critical role in supporting national security and global stability.", "WM": "Waste Management is a leading provider of waste management services in North America, offering collection, recycling, and disposal solutions to residential, commercial, and industrial customers. The company operates a network of landfills, transfer stations, and recycling facilities, and provides specialized services such as hazardous waste disposal and construction and demolition debris management. As a critical component of the waste management infrastructure, Waste Management plays a vital role in maintaining public health and environmental sustainability.", "UPS": "United Parcel Service (UPS) is a global logistics and transportation company providing a range of services including package delivery, freight transportation, and supply chain management. The company's key products and services include ground and air package delivery, freight forwarding, and logistics consulting, enabling businesses to efficiently manage their supply chains and reach customers worldwide. As a leading player in the logistics industry, UPS plays a critical role in facilitating global trade and commerce.", "EQIX": "Equinix is a global interconnection and data center company that provides colocation, interconnection, and managed services to businesses and organizations. The company operates a network of over 240 data centers across more than 70 markets worldwide, offering a range of products and services that enable customers to connect, interconnect, and distribute digital content, applications, and services. By providing a platform for digital businesses to scale and grow, Equinix plays a critical role in the global digital economy.", "ICE": "Intercontinental Exchange operates a global network of exchanges, clearing houses, and data services, facilitating the trading of financial, commodity, and currency markets. The company's key products and services include the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE), NYSE American, and ICE Futures, as well as data and analytics platforms. As a leading financial infrastructure provider, ICE plays a critical role in the global economy, enabling the efficient and transparent trading of securities and commodities.", "WMB": "Williams Companies is a leading energy infrastructure company that operates through three primary segments: Gas Gathering and Processing, Gas Pipelines, and NGL and Petchem Services. The company transports and processes natural gas, as well as produces and sells natural gas liquids (NGLs) and petchem products. As a critical component of the US energy infrastructure, Williams Companies plays a vital role in connecting domestic energy production to markets, supporting the country's energy independence and economic growth.", "WDC": "Western Digital is a global leader in the data storage industry, designing, manufacturing, and marketing a wide range of storage solutions, including hard disk drives, solid-state drives, and flash memory devices. The company's products are used in various applications, such as personal computers, data centers, and mobile devices, enabling the efficient storage and management of data. As a key player in the rapidly evolving data storage landscape, Western Digital plays a vital role in facilitating the growth of the digital economy.", "SNDK": "Western Digital Corporation, the successor to SanDisk, is a leading global data storage solutions provider. The company offers a range of products and services, including flash memory cards, USB drives, solid-state drives (SSDs), and external hard drives, catering to various industries such as consumer electronics, data centers, and automotive. As a key player in the data storage market, Western Digital's innovative solutions enable efficient data management and storage, driving the growth of emerging technologies like artificial intelligence, cloud computing, and the Internet of Things.", "MRSH": "Marsh McLennan is a global professional services firm providing risk, strategy, and human capital consulting to clients across various industries. The company's key products and services include risk and insurance services, talent and organizational consulting, and strategic risk and performance services, helping clients navigate complex business challenges. As a leading provider of advisory and solutions services, Marsh McLennan plays a crucial role in helping organizations mitigate risk, drive growth, and improve performance.", "MAR": "Marriott International is a multinational hospitality company that operates, franchises, and licenses a portfolio of brands across the lodging industry, including luxury, select-service, and budget-friendly options. The company's key products and services include hotel management, franchise agreements, and loyalty programs, catering to a diverse range of travelers and guests. As a leading player in the global hospitality market, Marriott International matters for its significant impact on the travel and tourism industry.", "JCI": "Johnson Controls is a multinational conglomerate that designs, manufactures, and installs building management systems, HVAC equipment, and fire suppression systems. The company's products and services help to optimize energy efficiency, safety, and comfort in buildings, serving industries such as healthcare, education, and commercial real estate. As a leading provider of smart and sustainable building solutions, Johnson Controls plays a critical role in reducing energy consumption and greenhouse gas emissions globally.", "SHW": "Sherwin-Williams is a leading global paints and coatings company that develops, manufactures, and distributes a wide range of products for the architectural, industrial, and consumer markets. The company's key products include paints, coatings, and related products for residential, commercial, and industrial applications. As a major player in the paints and coatings industry, Sherwin-Williams plays a significant role in shaping the built environment and driving innovation in the field of coatings technology.", "ADP": "Automatic Data Processing (ADP) is a provider of human capital management (HCM) solutions to businesses of all sizes. The company offers a range of products and services, including payroll processing, benefits administration, and talent management software, to help organizations manage their workforce and improve operational efficiency. As a leading HCM solutions provider, ADP plays a critical role in supporting the global economy by enabling businesses to effectively manage their human resources and make informed decisions.", "ECL": "Ecolab is a global leader in water, hygiene, and infection prevention solutions and services that protect people, brands, and the environment. The company provides a range of products and services, including cleaning and sanitizing solutions, water treatment and purification systems, and pest elimination services, primarily to the foodservice, hospitality, healthcare, and industrial markets. By helping customers reduce their environmental footprint and improve operational efficiency, Ecolab plays a critical role in promoting public health and sustainability.", "PNC": "PNC Financial Services is a diversified financial services organization that provides a range of products and services, including consumer and commercial banking, asset management, and wealth management. The company offers a variety of financial products and services to individuals, businesses, and government institutions, including deposit accounts, loans, credit cards, and investment services. As one of the largest banks in the United States, PNC Financial Services plays a significant role in the country's financial system, supporting economic growth and stability.", "USB": "U.S. Bancorp is a financial services holding company that provides a range of banking and financial services to individuals, businesses, and institutions. The company offers consumer and commercial banking, payment processing, mortgage banking, investment management, and other financial services through its subsidiaries, including U.S. Bank National Association. As one of the largest banking organizations in the United States, U.S. Bancorp plays a significant role in the country's financial system, supporting economic growth and stability.", "PWR": "Quanta Services is a leading provider of specialty contracting services, including infrastructure and network solutions, to the electric power, oil and gas, and communication industries. The company offers a range of services, including engineering, procurement, construction, and maintenance, as well as infrastructure development and network deployment. As a key player in the development of critical infrastructure, Quanta Services plays a vital role in supporting the growth and reliability of the energy and communication sectors.", "EMR": "Emerson Electric is a diversified global technology and industrial company that designs and manufactures a wide range of products and solutions for various industries, including process management, climate technologies, and automation solutions. The company's key products and services include valves, pumps, motors, and control systems, as well as software and consulting services. As a leading provider of technology and engineering solutions, Emerson Electric plays a critical role in enabling its customers to optimize their operations, improve efficiency, and reduce costs.", "BK": "BNY Mellon is a global financial services company that provides investment management, investment services, and wealth management solutions to institutions, corporations, and high net worth individuals. The company offers a range of products and services, including custody, accounting, and fund administration, as well as asset servicing, securities lending, and investment management. As one of the largest custodian banks in the world, BNY Mellon plays a critical role in facilitating global financial transactions and maintaining the integrity of financial markets.", "STX": "Seagate Technology is a global leader in data storage solutions, designing, manufacturing, and marketing hard disk drives (HDDs), solid-state drives (SSDs), and solid-state hybrid drives (SSHDs) for computing, consumer electronics, and enterprise applications. The company's products enable the storage and management of vast amounts of data across various industries, including cloud computing, artificial intelligence, and cybersecurity. As a key player in the data storage market, Seagate Technology plays a critical role in facilitating the growth of digital technologies and the increasing demand for data storage solutions.", "ITW": "Illinois Tool Works is a diversified multinational manufacturer of industrial products and equipment, offering a wide range of solutions to various industries including food equipment, construction, and automotive. Key products include fasteners, food processing equipment, and hydraulic systems, among others. As a leading industrial company, ITW plays a significant role in supporting global manufacturing and infrastructure development.", "MCO": "Moody's Corporation is a leading provider of credit ratings, research, and risk analysis for financial markets, offering insights and data to help investors, financial institutions, and corporations make informed decisions. The company's key products and services include credit ratings, credit research, and risk management solutions, as well as Moody's Analytics, a leading provider of financial intelligence. Moody's plays a critical role in maintaining the integrity of global financial markets by providing independent and objective credit assessments.", "REGN": "Regeneron Pharmaceuticals is a biopharmaceutical company that develops and commercializes medicines for the treatment of serious diseases, including eye disorders, cancer, and infectious diseases. The company's key products include Eylea, a treatment for age-related macular degeneration, and Libtayo, a skin cancer treatment. Regeneron's innovative therapies have improved the lives of millions of patients worldwide, solidifying its position as a leader in the biopharmaceutical industry.", "KKR": "KKR & Co. is a global investment firm that provides alternative asset management and private equity solutions to institutional and individual investors. The company offers a range of products and services, including private equity, credit, and real assets, as well as hedge funds and marketable alternative investments. As one of the largest alternative asset managers in the world, KKR & Co. plays a significant role in shaping the global economy through its investments and strategic partnerships.", "CDNS": "Cadence Design Systems is a leading provider of electronic design automation (EDA) software and intellectual property (IP) solutions, enabling the development of complex integrated circuits and systems-on-chip (SoCs). The company's products and services include digital and mixed-signal design tools, verification software, and IP cores, which are used by semiconductor companies and system designers worldwide. Cadence's solutions play a critical role in the development of advanced technologies, including artificial intelligence, 5G networks, and autonomous vehicles.", "RCL": "Royal Caribbean Group is a global cruise vacation company that operates a diverse portfolio of brands, including Royal Caribbean International, Celebrity Cruises, and Silversea Cruises. The company offers a range of onboard amenities and experiences, as well as shore excursions and land-based vacations, catering to diverse customer preferences and demographics. As a leading player in the cruise industry, Royal Caribbean Group matters for its significant economic impact and influence on global travel trends.", "MNST": "Monster Beverage Corporation is a leading manufacturer, marketer, and distributor of beverage products, primarily energy drinks and other non-carbonated beverages. The company's portfolio includes popular brands such as Monster Energy, NOS, Full Throttle, and Reign, among others. Monster Beverage's products are widely available in the United States, Canada, and internationally, making it a significant player in the global beverage market.", "MSI": "Motorola Solutions designs, manufactures, and supplies mission-critical communication solutions and services for public safety and commercial customers. The company's key products and services include two-way radios, body-worn cameras, and software platforms for public safety, as well as broadband and 5G network infrastructure for commercial customers. Motorola Solutions plays a critical role in enhancing public safety and enabling secure, reliable communication for emergency responders and critical infrastructure operations.", "CTAS": "Cintas is a leading provider of corporate identity uniforms and services, offering a range of products including uniforms, mats, mops, and other facility services. The company serves a diverse customer base across various industries, including healthcare, food service, and hospitality. By providing essential services and products, Cintas helps businesses maintain a professional image and operate efficiently.", "ORLY": "O'Reilly Automotive is a leading retailer of automotive aftermarket parts, tools, and supplies. The company operates a chain of stores offering a wide range of products, including new and remanufactured parts, tools, and accessories, as well as professional service provider offerings. As a key player in the automotive aftermarket industry, O'Reilly Automotive serves both do-it-yourself (DIY) and professional customers, providing essential products and services to support vehicle maintenance and repair.", "SNPS": "Synopsys is a leading provider of electronic design automation (EDA) software and intellectual property (IP) solutions for the semiconductor, automotive, aerospace, and industrial markets. The company's products and services enable designers and engineers to create complex electronic systems and semiconductor chips, driving innovation in areas such as artificial intelligence, 5G, and autonomous vehicles. As a critical enabler of the global electronics industry, Synopsys plays a vital role in advancing technology and improving people's lives.", "CSX": "CSX Corporation is a leading transportation company, providing rail-based freight transportation services to customers across a broad array of markets, including coal, agricultural and food products, construction materials, and intermodal. The company operates a network of approximately 21,000 miles of track and serves more than 70 ports and border crossings. As a critical component of the US supply chain, CSX plays a vital role in the movement of goods, supporting economic growth and development across the country.", "CMI": "Cummins Inc. is a global power technology leader that designs, manufactures, and distributes a wide range of power solutions, including diesel and natural gas engines, electric and hybrid powertrains, filtration, and power generation products. The company serves customers in the heavy-duty truck, bus, construction, agricultural, and industrial markets, as well as the energy and oil and gas industries. As a leading provider of clean and efficient power solutions, Cummins plays a critical role in enabling the transition to a more sustainable and environmentally friendly transportation and energy landscape.", "ABNB": "Airbnb is a global online marketplace for short-term vacation rentals, allowing users to book unique accommodations, experiences, and activities. The company's platform connects hosts who offer their properties, such as apartments, houses, and villas, with travelers seeking alternative lodging options. As a leader in the sharing economy, Airbnb has disrupted the traditional hospitality industry and transformed the way people travel and experience new destinations.", "CRH": "CRH plc is a multinational materials company that manufactures and supplies building materials, including aggregates, cement, and building materials solutions, to the construction industry. The company operates in over 30 countries globally and serves a diverse range of customers, from small builders to large infrastructure projects. As a leading supplier of building materials, CRH plays a critical role in supporting the construction of homes, commercial buildings, and infrastructure projects worldwide.", "MDLZ": "Mondelez International is a multinational confectionery, food, and beverage company that manufactures and distributes a diverse portfolio of iconic brands, including Oreo, Chips Ahoy, Trident, and Cadbury. The company operates in over 150 countries, offering a wide range of products in the snack, baking, and powdered beverage categories. As a leading player in the global consumer goods industry, Mondelez International plays a significant role in shaping consumer preferences and driving innovation in the food and beverage sector.", "CL": "Colgate-Palmolive is a multinational consumer goods company that develops, manufactures, and markets a range of personal care and household products, including toothpaste, toothbrushes, soaps, shampoos, and laundry detergents. The company's portfolio of well-known brands includes Colgate, Palmolive, and Irish Spring, among others. As a leading player in the consumer staples sector, Colgate-Palmolive provides essential products to households around the world, driving revenue growth and delivering value to shareholders.", "CI": "Cigna is a global health services organization that provides medical, dental, disability, and life insurance products and services to individuals, families, and employers. The company's key offerings include health insurance, pharmacy benefits management, and Medicare and Medicaid plans, as well as a range of specialty health services. As a major player in the health insurance industry, Cigna plays a significant role in shaping the delivery of healthcare services and improving health outcomes for its customers.", "DASH": "DoorDash is a technology company that provides food delivery and logistics services through its platform, connecting consumers with local restaurants and food establishments. The company's key products and services include its on-demand delivery platform, DashPass subscription service, and DasherDirect payment platform. By streamlining food delivery and expanding access to local cuisine, DoorDash has become a leading player in the rapidly growing food delivery market.", "KMI": "Kinder Morgan is a leading energy infrastructure company that operates a vast network of pipelines, terminals, and storage facilities, transporting and storing natural gas, crude oil, and other petroleum products across North America. The company's key products and services include pipeline transportation, terminal and storage operations, and carbon capture and storage solutions. As a critical component of the energy infrastructure, Kinder Morgan plays a vital role in connecting producers with consumers, supporting the growth of the energy industry, and promoting economic development.", "TDG": "TransDigm Group is a leading global designer, producer, and supplier of highly engineered aerospace components, systems, and subsystems. The company's products and services cater to the commercial and military aerospace markets, including aircraft systems, power and control systems, and other specialized components. TransDigm's offerings enable the safe and efficient operation of aircraft, supporting the global air transportation network and military operations.", "AEP": "American Electric Power is a diversified energy company that generates, transmits, and distributes electricity to approximately 5.4 million customers across 11 states in the US. The company's key products and services include electricity generation from coal, natural gas, nuclear, and renewable sources, as well as transmission and distribution services. As one of the largest electric utilities in the US, AEP plays a critical role in meeting the country's growing energy demands while promoting a more sustainable energy future.", "COR": "Cencora is a pharmaceutical company that develops, manufactures, and commercializes a portfolio of generic and specialty pharmaceutical products, including respiratory and dermatology treatments. The company's product offerings include a range of generic and branded medications, as well as a pipeline of in-development products. As a leading player in the pharmaceutical industry, Cencora plays a critical role in providing affordable and accessible healthcare solutions to patients worldwide.", "AON": "Aon plc is a global professional services firm providing risk management, human resources, and retirement solutions to clients. The company's key products and services include insurance brokerage, reinsurance brokerage, and human capital consulting, helping clients navigate complex risks and optimize their benefits. As one of the largest insurance brokers worldwide, Aon plays a significant role in shaping the global risk landscape and advising clients on strategic business decisions.", "HLT": "Hilton Worldwide is a multinational hospitality company that operates a portfolio of 18 world-class brands, including Hilton Hotels & Resorts, Waldorf Astoria Hotels & Resorts, and Hampton by Hilton, offering a range of accommodations and services to leisure and business travelers. The company's global network of over 6,300 properties across 123 countries provides guests with a consistent and high-quality experience. As a leading player in the hospitality industry, Hilton Worldwide matters to travelers and investors alike, offering a unique combination of brand recognition, operational scale, and growth opportunities.", "GM": "General Motors is a multinational corporation that designs, manufactures, and sells vehicles and vehicle parts worldwide. The company's key products include passenger cars, light trucks, and electric vehicles under various brands such as Chevrolet, Buick, GMC, and Cadillac. As one of the world's largest automakers, General Motors plays a significant role in shaping the global automotive industry and driving innovation in electric and autonomous vehicle technologies.", "HOOD": "Robinhood Markets is a financial technology company that offers commission-free trading and investing services to retail customers through its mobile app and website. The company's key products and services include its self-guided trading platform, cryptocurrency trading, and cash management accounts. By democratizing access to the financial markets, Robinhood has disrupted the traditional brokerage industry and made investing more accessible to a wider range of consumers.", "NSC": "Norfolk Southern Corporation is a leading transportation provider in North America, operating a network of approximately 21,000 miles of track in 22 states, the District of Columbia, and Ontario, Canada. The company offers a range of services, including rail transportation of coal, intermodal, and merchandise freight, as well as logistics and supply chain management solutions. As a critical component of the nation's supply chain, Norfolk Southern plays a vital role in facilitating the movement of goods and commerce across the United States and Canada.", "RSG": "Republic Services is a diversified waste management company that provides collection, transfer, disposal, and recycling services to municipal, commercial, and industrial customers. The company offers a range of services, including trash collection, recycling, and landfill operations, serving over 14 million customers across the United States. As a leading provider of waste management solutions, Republic Services plays a critical role in maintaining public health and safety, as well as promoting environmental sustainability.", "CVNA": "Carvana is an e-commerce platform that enables customers to purchase, finance, and service used vehicles online, offering a wide selection of vehicles and transparent pricing. The company's key products and services include its online marketplace, Carvana.com, as well as its network of physical vending machines and retail stores. By streamlining the car-buying process, Carvana has disrupted the traditional automotive retail industry and become a leading player in the used vehicle market.", "WBD": "Warner Bros. Discovery is a global media and entertainment company that operates through various segments, including Warner Bros., HBO, Discovery Channel, and more. The company produces and distributes content across film, television, and digital platforms, offering a range of products and services including movies, television shows, documentaries, and news programming. As a leading player in the global media landscape, Warner Bros. Discovery matters for its significant influence on popular culture and its ability to shape the entertainment industry through innovative content and business strategies.", "LHX": "L3Harris Technologies is a leading global aerospace and defense technology company that provides a broad portfolio of communication, electronic warfare, navigation, and other mission-critical solutions for military, government, and commercial customers. The company's products and services include tactical communications, electronic warfare systems, navigation systems, and cybersecurity solutions. As a major player in the defense industry, L3Harris plays a critical role in supporting national security and global defense efforts.", "TRV": "The Travelers Companies, Inc. is a leading provider of property casualty insurance products and services to businesses, individuals, and institutions worldwide. The company offers a range of insurance products, including commercial property, casualty, and specialty insurance, as well as surety and fidelity bonds. As one of the largest property casualty insurance companies in the US, Travelers plays a significant role in protecting businesses and individuals from financial losses due to accidents, natural disasters, and other unforeseen events.", "ELV": "Elevance Health is a health benefits company that provides a range of products and services, including health insurance, pharmacy benefits management, and care management, to individuals, employers, and government programs. The company's offerings include UnitedHealthcare, Optum, and other brands, providing access to healthcare services, pharmacy benefits, and data-driven insights to improve health outcomes. As one of the largest health insurance companies in the US, Elevance Health plays a critical role in shaping the nation's healthcare landscape.", "ROST": "Ross Stores is a leading off-price apparel and home fashion retailer operating under the Ross Dress for Less and dd's DISCOUNTS banners. The company offers a wide selection of brand-name and designer merchandise at discounted prices, catering to value-conscious consumers. By providing affordable fashion options, Ross Stores has become a significant player in the retail industry, offering customers a unique shopping experience and driving sales growth through its efficient supply chain and merchandising strategies.", "VLO": "Valero Energy is a Fortune 500 energy company that operates as an independent petroleum refiner and marketer of transportation fuels and other petrochemical products. The company's key products include gasoline, diesel fuel, jet fuel, and other refined petroleum products, as well as renewable diesel and ethanol. As one of the largest refiners in the United States, Valero Energy plays a significant role in meeting the country's energy demands and contributing to the global energy market.", "PCAR": "Paccar Inc is a global leader in the design, manufacture, and distribution of heavy-duty trucks, light trucks, bus, and winch products. The company's key brands include Kenworth, Peterbilt, and DAF, offering a range of commercial vehicles that cater to various industries and applications. As a major player in the global trucking industry, Paccar's products and services play a critical role in facilitating the movement of goods and people, supporting economic growth and development.", "BKR": "Baker Hughes is a leading energy technology company that provides integrated oilfield products, services, and digital solutions to the global energy industry. The company's offerings include drilling and production systems, pressure pumping, and artificial lift systems, as well as digital solutions for energy management and optimization. As a key player in the energy sector, Baker Hughes plays a critical role in meeting the world's growing energy demands while promoting operational efficiency and environmental sustainability.", "AZO": "AutoZone is a leading retailer of automotive replacement parts and accessories in the United States. The company operates a chain of stores offering a wide range of products, including new and remanufactured automotive parts, batteries, accessories, and maintenance items. As a major player in the automotive aftermarket industry, AutoZone provides essential products and services to car owners and repair shops, driving growth and profitability in the sector.", "PSX": "Phillips 66 is an energy manufacturing and logistics company that refines, transports, and markets petroleum products, as well as produces chemicals and fuels. The company's key products include gasoline, diesel fuel, jet fuel, and lubricants, which are distributed through a network of refineries, pipelines, and terminals. As a leading energy company, Phillips 66 plays a crucial role in meeting global energy demands and supporting economic growth.", "TFC": "Truist Financial is a bank holding company that provides a range of financial services, including personal and commercial banking, investment, mortgage, and insurance products. The company operates through its subsidiaries, offering deposit, loan, and payment services, as well as wealth management and capital markets capabilities. As one of the largest banks in the US, Truist Financial plays a significant role in facilitating economic growth and financial stability for its customers and communities.", "BDX": "Becton Dickinson is a global medical technology company that develops, manufactures, and sells medical devices, diagnostic instruments, and pharmaceutical packaging solutions. Its key products include syringes, needles, and infusion therapy systems, as well as molecular diagnostics and point-of-care testing systems. As a leading provider of medical technology, Becton Dickinson plays a critical role in advancing healthcare outcomes and improving patient care worldwide.", "SRE": "Sempra is a multinational energy company that engages in the production, transportation, and sale of electricity, natural gas, and liquefied natural gas. The company's key products and services include electricity generation, natural gas storage, and liquefied natural gas export, with operations in the United States, Mexico, and the United Kingdom. As a leading energy infrastructure company, Sempra plays a critical role in meeting global energy demand and supporting economic growth.", "MPC": "Marathon Petroleum is a leading energy company that operates a nationwide portfolio of midstream, refining, and retail businesses. The company's key products and services include refining and marketing petroleum products, transporting crude oil and petroleum products, and operating a network of retail gasoline stations. As one of the largest refiners in the United States, Marathon Petroleum plays a critical role in meeting the country's energy demands.", "APO": "Apollo Global Management is a leading global alternative investment manager that provides private equity, credit, and real assets solutions to investors worldwide. The company offers a range of investment products and services, including private equity funds, credit funds, and real assets funds, which cater to the diverse needs of institutional and individual investors. As one of the largest alternative investment managers, Apollo plays a significant role in shaping the global investment landscape through its innovative investment strategies and expertise.", "TEL": "TE Connectivity is a global technology leader that designs and manufactures connectivity and sensing solutions for a wide range of industries, including automotive, industrial equipment, aerospace, defense, healthcare, and energy. The company offers a diverse portfolio of products and services, including connectors, sensors, and wireless connectivity solutions. As a leading provider of critical infrastructure and connectivity solutions, TE Connectivity plays a vital role in enabling the development and deployment of advanced technologies that transform industries and improve lives.", "APD": "Air Products is a global industrial gases company that supplies a range of products and services, including atmospheric gases, process gases, and equipment, to various industries such as energy, healthcare, and manufacturing. The company's key products include oxygen, nitrogen, argon, and carbon dioxide, as well as equipment for gas processing and handling. By providing essential gases and related technologies, Air Products enables its customers to improve efficiency, productivity, and safety in their operations.", "FTNT": "Fortinet is a cybersecurity solutions provider that helps protect organizations from cyber threats through its network security, endpoint security, and cloud security products. The company's key offerings include its FortiGate network security appliances, FortiGuard security services, and FortiClient endpoint security software. By providing comprehensive security solutions, Fortinet enables businesses to safeguard their networks, data, and applications, and stay ahead of the evolving threat landscape.", "AFL": "Aflac is a supplemental insurance company providing financial protection to individuals and families in the event of illness or injury. The company's key products and services include cancer, accident, and life insurance policies, as well as dental and vision insurance plans. Aflac's policies provide financial support to policyholders during difficult times, helping to alleviate the financial burden associated with medical expenses.", "AJG": "Arthur J. Gallagher & Co. is a global insurance brokerage and risk management services firm providing a range of products and services, including property and casualty insurance, employee benefits, and risk management consulting. The company serves clients across various industries, helping them manage their insurance and risk needs. As one of the largest insurance brokerages in the world, Gallagher & Co. plays a significant role in shaping the global insurance market.", "VST": "Vistra Corp operates as a wholesale electricity provider in the United States, offering a range of products and services including electricity generation, transmission, and distribution, as well as energy trading and retail electricity sales. The company owns and operates a diverse fleet of power generation assets, including coal, natural gas, and solar facilities. As a leading player in the US electricity market, Vistra Corp plays a critical role in meeting the country's growing energy demands.", "ZTS": "Zoetis is a leading global animal health company that develops, manufactures, and commercializes a wide range of veterinary vaccines, medicines, and diagnostics for livestock and companion animals. The company's product portfolio includes prescription and over-the-counter medications, as well as vaccines and biologic products for various species, including cattle, pigs, poultry, and companion animals. By providing innovative solutions to improve animal health and well-being, Zoetis plays a critical role in supporting the global food supply and advancing the human-animal bond.", "NXPI": "NXP Semiconductors is a leading global semiconductor company that designs, develops, and manufactures high-performance, mixed-signal integrated circuits and other semiconductor solutions. The company's product portfolio includes automotive, industrial, mobile, and Internet of Things (IoT) solutions, as well as secure identification, automotive radar, and radio frequency (RF) products. NXP's innovative semiconductor solutions enable the development of advanced technologies that transform industries and improve people's lives.", "ALL": "Allstate Corporation is a leading insurance company that provides a range of personal and commercial property-liability insurance products, including auto, home, and life insurance, as well as financial services. The company's key products and services include auto and home insurance, life insurance, and retirement savings plans. As one of the largest publicly traded insurance companies in the US, Allstate plays a significant role in protecting consumers and businesses from financial risks.", "AME": "Ametek is a leading global manufacturer of electronic instruments and electromechanical devices with a diverse range of products serving industrial, aerospace, defense, and other markets. The company's key offerings include process analytical instruments, process control systems, and electromechanical devices, among others. Ametek's products play a critical role in various industries, enabling customers to improve efficiency, productivity, and safety.", "PSA": "Public Storage is a real estate investment trust that owns and operates self-storage facilities across the United States. The company offers a range of storage solutions, including traditional storage units, climate-controlled storage, and vehicle storage, providing individuals and businesses with secure and convenient storage options. As one of the largest self-storage operators in the country, Public Storage plays a significant role in the storage industry, catering to the growing demand for flexible and accessible storage solutions.", "MPWR": "Monolithic Power Systems is a technology company that designs, develops, and markets high-performance power solutions for the semiconductor industry. The company's key products include DC-DC converters, LED drivers, and power management ICs, which are used in a variety of applications including consumer electronics, data centers, and renewable energy systems. By providing efficient and reliable power solutions, Monolithic Power Systems enables the development of smaller, faster, and more energy-efficient electronic devices.", "GWW": "W.W. Grainger is a leading industrial supply company that provides products, services, and solutions to businesses and institutions. The company offers a wide range of products, including tools, equipment, and supplies, as well as services such as inventory management and supply chain solutions. As a major distributor of industrial products, Grainger plays a critical role in supporting the operations and maintenance of businesses across various industries.", "CAH": "Cardinal Health is a multinational healthcare services and products company that provides pharmaceuticals, medical supplies, and health information technology solutions to hospitals, pharmacies, and healthcare providers. The company offers a range of products and services, including generic and branded medications, medical and surgical supplies, and clinical and business process outsourcing solutions. As a leading healthcare distributor, Cardinal Health plays a critical role in ensuring the availability and accessibility of essential healthcare products and services.", "CTVA": "Corteva, Inc. is a global agriculture company that develops and markets seeds, crop protection products, and digital solutions to help farmers improve crop yields and reduce environmental impact. The company's portfolio includes popular seed brands such as Pioneer and Brevant, as well as crop protection products like insecticides and herbicides. By providing innovative solutions to the agricultural industry, Corteva plays a critical role in meeting the world's growing demand for food and other agricultural products.", "OKE": "Oneok is a diversified energy company that operates through three business segments: natural gas gathering, processing, and transportation; natural gas liquids (NGLs) marketing; and natural gas and NGLs marketing. The company transports, stores, and markets natural gas and NGLs, providing critical infrastructure for the energy industry. As a major energy infrastructure provider, Oneok plays a vital role in connecting energy producers with consumers, supporting the efficient and reliable delivery of natural gas and NGLs.", "OXY": "Occidental Petroleum is a multinational energy company that explores, produces, and markets crude oil, natural gas liquids, and natural gas. The company operates in the United States, the Middle East, and other regions, with a focus on unconventional oil and gas production. As one of the largest oil and gas producers in the United States, Occidental Petroleum plays a significant role in meeting global energy demands.", "FAST": "Fastenal is a leading industrial distributor of fasteners and other industrial and construction supplies, offering a wide range of products including nuts, bolts, screws, and other related items. The company serves a diverse customer base across various industries, including manufacturing, construction, and oil and gas. As a key supplier to the industrial sector, Fastenal plays a critical role in supporting the production and maintenance of essential infrastructure and equipment.", "F": "Ford Motor Company is a multinational automaker that designs, manufactures, and markets vehicles and mobility solutions worldwide. The company offers a range of products, including passenger cars, commercial vehicles, and electric vehicles, with popular brands such as Ford, Lincoln, and Mustang. As one of the largest and most iconic automakers globally, Ford plays a significant role in shaping the automotive industry and driving innovation in sustainable mobility solutions.", "KEYS": "Keysight Technologies is a leading technology company that designs, manufactures, and markets electronic design and test equipment, software, and services for the aerospace, automotive, energy, industrial, communications, and semiconductor industries. The company's products and solutions enable customers to accelerate innovation and improve product quality by streamlining the design and test process. Keysight's solutions are critical to the development and deployment of emerging technologies such as 5G, artificial intelligence, and the Internet of Things (IoT).", "CARR": "Carrier Global Corporation is a leading global provider of healthy, safe, and sustainable building and refrigeration solutions, offering a diverse portfolio of products and services that include air conditioning, heating, ventilation, refrigeration, and fire and security systems. The company's solutions are used in various industries, including commercial, industrial, and residential markets, and are designed to improve indoor air quality, energy efficiency, and occupant comfort. As a leader in the built environment, Carrier Global plays a critical role in shaping the future of sustainable and resilient buildings.", "ADSK": "Autodesk is a global leader in the design, development, and manufacturing of software for building information modeling, computer-aided design, computer-aided engineering, and computer-aided manufacturing. The company's flagship products include AutoCAD, Revit, Inventor, and Fusion 360, which enable architects, engineers, and manufacturers to create, visualize, and simulate digital models of real-world objects. By providing innovative software solutions, Autodesk empowers users to design, build, and deliver innovative projects more efficiently and sustainably.", "URI": "United Rentals is a leading equipment rental company that provides a wide range of equipment and services to construction, industrial, and oil and gas customers across North America. The company offers a diverse fleet of equipment, including aerial lifts, cranes, forklifts, and generators, as well as services such as equipment maintenance and repair. By providing access to equipment and expertise, United Rentals helps customers manage their capital and labor costs, enabling them to focus on their core business operations.", "TRGP": "Targa Resources is a midstream energy company that operates a network of pipelines, storage facilities, and terminals primarily in the United States. The company provides natural gas and natural gas liquids (NGLs) gathering, processing, and transportation services, as well as NGLs fractionation and marketing services. As a leading midstream provider, Targa Resources plays a critical role in connecting the production of oil and natural gas to the markets that consume it.", "EW": "Edwards Lifesciences is a global leader in the development, manufacture, and marketing of innovative medical solutions for minimally invasive procedures in cardiology, critical care, and surgical specialties. The company's key products include heart valves, transcatheter heart valves, and critical care monitoring systems, which help improve patient outcomes and quality of life. Edwards Lifesciences plays a critical role in advancing the treatment of cardiovascular disease and critical care conditions.", "FANG": "Diamondback Energy is an independent oil and natural gas company engaged in the acquisition, development, exploration, and production of oil and natural gas properties in the Permian Basin in West Texas. The company's primary products include crude oil, natural gas, and natural gas liquids. As a leading player in the Permian Basin, Diamondback Energy plays a significant role in meeting the world's growing energy demands.", "EXC": "Exelon is a utility company that generates, transmits, and distributes energy to residential, commercial, and industrial customers. Its key products and services include electricity and natural gas, as well as energy efficiency and renewable energy solutions. As one of the largest energy companies in the US, Exelon plays a critical role in meeting the country's growing energy demands while promoting a cleaner and more sustainable energy future.", "IDXX": "Idexx Laboratories is a global leader in veterinary diagnostics and software for animal health. The company offers a range of products and services, including in-clinic and at-home testing solutions, as well as practice management software and data analytics tools for veterinarians. By providing critical diagnostic information and insights, Idexx Laboratories helps veterinarians improve the health and well-being of animals, driving better outcomes for pet owners and the veterinary community.", "EA": "Electronic Arts is a leading global interactive entertainment company that develops, markets, and distributes video games for various platforms, including console systems, personal computers, and mobile devices. The company's key products and services include popular franchises such as FIFA, Madden NFL, The Sims, and Battlefield, as well as its EA Sports and EA Games labels. As a major player in the gaming industry, EA matters for its significant influence on the global gaming market and its ability to create engaging experiences for millions of players worldwide.", "FIX": "Comfort Systems USA is a leading provider of commercial and industrial mechanical services, offering heating, ventilation, air conditioning, plumbing, and controls services to a diverse range of industries. The company serves clients through its network of regional offices and operates in over 120 locations across the United States and Canada. As a major player in the mechanical services sector, Comfort Systems USA plays a critical role in maintaining and improving the infrastructure of commercial and industrial facilities nationwide.", "TER": "Teradyne is a leading provider of industrial automation and collaborative robots, offering a range of products and services that enable companies to improve efficiency and productivity in various industries. The company's key products include the Universal Robots brand of collaborative robots, as well as its own autonomous mobile robots and machine learning software. Teradyne's innovative solutions matter as they help manufacturers adapt to changing workforce dynamics and increasing demand for automation.", "CIEN": "Ciena Corporation is a network equipment, software, and services company that designs, develops, and sells networking and communications equipment, software, and services for telecommunications service providers, cable operators, and large enterprises. The company's key products include packet-optical networking platforms, software-defined networking (SDN) and network functions virtualization (NFV) solutions, and network management software. Ciena's solutions enable high-speed data transmission and help service providers and enterprises deliver high-bandwidth, low-latency services.", "NDAQ": "Nasdaq, Inc. operates a global technology and information services company serving capital markets, corporate customers, and the financial community. The company provides trading, clearing, exchange technology, regulatory, compliance, and corporate solutions through its various platforms, including the Nasdaq stock exchange. As a leading provider of financial infrastructure and data, Nasdaq plays a critical role in facilitating global capital markets and supporting economic growth.", "XEL": "Xcel Energy is a utility company that generates, transmits, and distributes electricity and natural gas to residential, commercial, and industrial customers in the United States. The company's key products and services include electricity and natural gas supply, transmission and distribution, and energy efficiency solutions. As one of the largest utility companies in the US, Xcel Energy plays a critical role in meeting the country's energy needs and promoting a more sustainable energy future.", "COIN": "Coinbase is a digital currency exchange and financial services company that enables users to buy, sell, store, and trade cryptocurrencies such as Bitcoin, Ethereum, and others. The company's key products and services include its exchange platform, wallet, and custody solutions, as well as its institutional-grade trading and custody services for professional investors. As a leading player in the rapidly growing digital asset market, Coinbase plays a critical role in facilitating the adoption and mainstream acceptance of cryptocurrencies.", "ETR": "Entergy Corporation is a diversified utility company that generates, transmits, and distributes electricity to approximately 2.9 million customers across the southern United States. The company's key products and services include nuclear, fossil fuel, and renewable energy generation, as well as transmission and distribution services. As one of the largest utilities in the country, Entergy plays a critical role in meeting the energy needs of its customers and contributing to the regional economy.", "GRMN": "Garmin Ltd. is a global technology company that designs, manufactures, and markets navigation, communication, and information devices. The company's key products include GPS navigation systems, smartwatches, fitness trackers, and aviation electronics, among others. As a leading provider of innovative navigation and wearable technology solutions, Garmin plays a significant role in the consumer electronics industry.", "MET": "MetLife is a global life insurance company that provides a range of financial services and products, including life insurance, annuities, employee benefits, and asset management. The company serves individual and institutional clients through its global distribution network, offering solutions for retirement, insurance, and investment needs. As one of the largest life insurers in the world, MetLife plays a significant role in helping individuals and organizations manage risk and achieve long-term financial security.", "HSY": "The Hershey Company is a leading American multinational consumer goods company that develops, manufactures, markets, and sells a wide range of chocolate and non-chocolate confectionery products, as well as snack foods and beverages. Key products include Hershey's Milk Chocolate bars, Reese's Peanut Butter Cups, and Kisses, among others. As one of the largest chocolate manufacturers in North America, the company plays a significant role in the global confectionery industry.", "CMG": "Chipotle Mexican Grill is a fast-casual restaurant chain that specializes in Mexican-inspired food, offering burritos, bowls, tacos, salads, and other menu items made with responsibly sourced ingredients. The company operates over 2,000 locations globally, focusing on serving high-quality, sustainably sourced food to customers seeking a convenient and flavorful dining experience. As a leader in the fast-casual segment, Chipotle Mexican Grill matters to investors due to its strong brand recognition and growing demand for its unique offerings.", "ROK": "Rockwell Automation is a leading industrial automation company that designs, builds, and supports industrial automation and information solutions, including hardware, software, and services, to help manufacturers optimize their production processes. The company's key products and services include programmable logic controllers, human-machine interfaces, and industrial software, as well as its FactoryTalk and FactorySphere platforms. By enabling industrial automation, Rockwell Automation helps manufacturers improve efficiency, productivity, and quality, making it a critical component of the global manufacturing ecosystem.", "YUM": "Yum! Brands is a multinational fast-food corporation that operates a portfolio of popular brands, including KFC, Pizza Hut, and Taco Bell, offering a range of quick-service and casual dining options to customers worldwide. The company's brands are known for their iconic flavors and convenience, catering to diverse consumer preferences and lifestyles. As a leading player in the fast-food industry, Yum! Brands matters for its significant market presence, brand recognition, and ability to drive growth through innovation and expansion.", "AXON": "Axon Enterprise is a technology company that develops and manufactures less-lethal weapons, body cameras, and software solutions for law enforcement, public safety, and military organizations. The company's key products include the Taser brand of stun guns, body cameras, and evidence management software, which enable agencies to collect, store, and analyze data. Axon Enterprise's technology helps improve public safety and reduce the use of force by law enforcement.", "KR": "Kroger operates as a retailer, offering a range of products including grocery, pharmacy, and general merchandise through its supermarkets, multi-department stores, and specialty stores. The company's key products and services include private-label brands, digital shopping platforms, and pharmacy services. As one of the largest retailers in the United States, Kroger plays a significant role in the country's food retail market, serving millions of customers nationwide.", "WAB": "Wabtec Corporation is a leading provider of value-added, technology-based equipment, systems, and services for the global rail and transit industries. The company's portfolio includes locomotives, freight cars, transit equipment, and services such as maintenance, repair, and modernization. Wabtec plays a critical role in enabling the efficient movement of people and goods, supporting the growth of global commerce and transportation infrastructure.", "FITB": "Fifth Third Bancorp is a diversified bank holding company that provides a range of financial services, including commercial and retail banking, wealth management, and investment services. The company offers deposit products, commercial lending, and investment services to individuals, businesses, and institutions through its network of branches and online channels. As one of the largest banks in the Midwest, Fifth Third plays a significant role in the regional economy and financial markets.", "DHI": "D. R. Horton is a leading homebuilder in the United States, operating in 27 states and 84 markets. The company designs, builds, and sells single-family homes, townhomes, and condominiums through its various brands, catering to a wide range of consumers. As one of the largest homebuilders in the country, D. R. Horton plays a significant role in shaping the US housing market and providing affordable housing options for millions of Americans.", "AMP": "Ameriprise Financial is a diversified financial services company that provides financial planning, asset management, and insurance products to individuals, families, and small businesses. The company offers a range of products and services, including investment management, retirement planning, estate planning, and insurance solutions. As a leading provider of financial services, Ameriprise Financial helps clients achieve their financial goals and secure their financial futures.", "AIG": "American International Group (AIG) is a leading global insurance organization providing a wide range of insurance products and services to individuals and businesses worldwide. The company's key products include property and casualty insurance, life insurance, and retirement savings products, as well as financial services and asset management. As one of the largest insurance companies globally, AIG plays a significant role in managing risk and providing financial security to its customers and stakeholders.", "SYY": "Sysco is a leading food distribution company that provides a wide range of food and related products to the foodservice industry, including restaurants, healthcare and educational facilities, and hospitality providers. The company offers over 400,000 products, including meat, produce, dairy products, and dry goods, as well as supply chain solutions and culinary expertise. As a major player in the food distribution market, Sysco plays a critical role in ensuring the availability of fresh and high-quality food products to customers across the globe.", "ODFL": "Old Dominion Freight Line, Inc. is a leading less-than-truckload (LTL) motor carrier providing regional, inter-regional, and national LTL services to a broad range of markets. The company offers a variety of services, including ground and air freight, warehousing and logistics, and supply chain management. As one of the largest LTL carriers in the US, Old Dominion plays a critical role in the nation's supply chain infrastructure, connecting businesses and consumers across the country.", "CBRE": "CBRE Group is a global real estate services and investment company that provides a range of services including commercial property sales, leasing, and property management, as well as valuation, consulting, and investment management. The company's key products and services include commercial property brokerage, facilities management, and project management, among others. As one of the largest commercial real estate services companies in the world, CBRE plays a significant role in shaping the global commercial real estate market and providing strategic solutions to its clients.", "PEG": "Public Service Enterprise Group (PEG) is a diversified energy company that operates in the Northeast and Mid-Atlantic regions of the United States, providing electricity and gas to approximately 10 million customers. The company generates, transmits, and distributes electricity, as well as supplies gas to residential, commercial, and industrial customers. As a leading utility company, PEG plays a critical role in meeting the energy needs of its customers and supporting economic growth in the regions it serves.", "MSCI": "MSCI Inc. is a leading provider of critical decision support tools and services for investment professionals around the world. The company offers a range of products and services, including indexes, portfolio risk and performance analytics, and environmental, social and governance (ESG) research, to help investors make informed investment decisions. By providing data-driven insights, MSCI helps investors navigate global markets and achieve their investment goals.", "PYPL": "PayPal Holdings, Inc. is a digital payments company that enables individuals and businesses to send and receive payments online. The company's key products and services include PayPal, Venmo, and Braintree, which facilitate online transactions, mobile payments, and cross-border payments. As a leading online payment platform, PayPal plays a significant role in the digital economy, connecting buyers and sellers worldwide.", "PCG": "PG&E Corporation is a holding company that operates through its principal subsidiary, Pacific Gas and Electric Company, providing electricity and natural gas to approximately 16 million customers in Northern and Central California. The company offers a range of products and services, including electricity and natural gas supply, transmission and distribution, and energy efficiency and renewable energy solutions. As one of the largest combined natural gas and electric utility companies in the United States, PG&E Corporation plays a critical role in meeting the energy needs of its customers and supporting the economic and environmental sustainability of the region.", "DAL": "Delta Air Lines is a major American airline that operates a network of domestic and international routes, providing air transportation services to passengers and cargo. The company's key products and services include scheduled air transportation, cargo transportation, and loyalty programs. As one of the world's largest airlines, Delta plays a significant role in connecting people and businesses across the globe, driving economic growth and development.", "VTR": "Ventas is a healthcare real estate investment trust that invests in and owns a diversified portfolio of medical office buildings, senior housing, and healthcare facilities. The company's key products and services include leasing properties to healthcare providers and operators, as well as providing financing and other services to its tenants. As a leading player in the healthcare real estate sector, Ventas plays a critical role in supporting the delivery of high-quality patient care and improving healthcare outcomes.", "KDP": "Keurig Dr Pepper is a leading beverage company that operates in the United States and Canada, offering a diverse portfolio of hot and cold beverages, including coffee, tea, water, juice, and soda. The company's key brands include Keurig, Dr Pepper, 7 Up, Snapple, and A&W, among others. As a major player in the beverage industry, Keurig Dr Pepper matters to consumers and investors alike, providing a wide range of popular brands and innovative products.", "ED": "Consolidated Edison is a utility company that generates, transmits, and distributes electricity, as well as distributes natural gas to residential, commercial, and industrial customers in New York City and surrounding areas. The company's key products and services include electricity and natural gas distribution, as well as energy-related services such as energy efficiency and renewable energy solutions. As a major provider of essential energy services, Consolidated Edison plays a critical role in powering the economy and daily life in the New York metropolitan region.", "VMC": "Vulcan Materials Company is a leading producer of construction aggregates, including crushed stone, sand, and gravel, as well as asphalt mix and cement. The company supplies essential materials to the construction industry, supporting infrastructure development, housing, and commercial projects. As a major player in the US construction materials market, Vulcan Materials plays a critical role in building the nation's infrastructure and driving economic growth.", "EBAY": "eBay Inc. is a global e-commerce company that operates a platform for the sale of goods and services by third-party sellers. The company's key products and services include its online marketplace, PayPal payment processing, and various mobile apps. As a leading online marketplace, eBay connects buyers and sellers worldwide, facilitating the exchange of goods and services and driving consumer spending.", "CCL": "Carnival Corporation & plc is a global cruise company that operates a fleet of cruise ships offering a range of onboard amenities and itineraries to destinations worldwide. The company's key products and services include cruise vacations, onboard dining and entertainment, and shore excursions. As one of the largest cruise operators in the world, Carnival plays a significant role in the global travel and leisure industry.", "MCHP": "Microchip Technology is a leading provider of semiconductor solutions for various embedded control applications, offering a wide range of products including microcontrollers, analog and interface products, and wireless and security products. The company's products are used in a variety of industries, including automotive, industrial, aerospace, communications, and consumer electronics. As a key supplier of semiconductor solutions, Microchip Technology plays a critical role in enabling the development of connected, secure, and efficient devices that power modern technology.", "MLM": "Martin Marietta Materials is a leading supplier of aggregates products, including crushed stone, sand, and gravel, as well as a producer of cement and other construction materials. The company serves a diverse range of end markets, including the construction, infrastructure, and energy industries. As a major player in the US aggregates market, Martin Marietta Materials plays a critical role in supporting the nation's infrastructure development and growth.", "TTWO": "Take-Two Interactive is a global video game publisher and developer that designs, develops, publishes, and markets entertainment software worldwide. The company's portfolio includes popular franchises such as Grand Theft Auto, Red Dead, NBA 2K, and Borderlands, among others. Take-Two Interactive is a leading player in the gaming industry, known for its high-quality and engaging games that drive revenue and user engagement.", "HIG": "The Hartford Financial Services Group, Inc. is a multinational insurance and financial services company that provides property and casualty insurance, group benefits, mortgage insurance, and investment products to individuals and businesses. The company's key products and services include auto, home, and workers' compensation insurance, as well as group life and disability insurance. As a leading insurance provider, The Hartford plays a significant role in protecting individuals and businesses from financial risks, making it a vital component of the global financial ecosystem.", "CCI": "Crown Castle is a real estate investment trust that owns, operates, and leases cell towers and other wireless infrastructure across the United States and Australia. The company's portfolio consists of over 40,000 cell towers and 80,000 small cells, providing critical connectivity infrastructure to wireless carriers and other tenants. Crown Castle's assets support the growing demand for wireless data and enable the expansion of 5G networks, making it a key player in the telecommunications industry.", "DDOG": "Datadog is a cloud-based monitoring and analytics platform that provides real-time insights into software applications and infrastructure performance. The company's key products and services include its eponymous platform, which offers monitoring, logging, and security capabilities, as well as its Synthetics product for automated end-to-end monitoring. By providing a unified view of application performance, Datadog enables businesses to optimize their technology operations and make data-driven decisions.", "NRG": "NRG Energy is a leading integrated power company that generates, sells, and delivers energy and energy solutions to approximately 3.7 million residential, commercial, and industrial customers across the United States. The company operates a diverse portfolio of power generation assets, including natural gas, wind, and solar facilities, as well as a retail electricity business that offers a range of energy products and services. As one of the largest energy companies in the US, NRG Energy plays a critical role in meeting the country's growing energy demands while promoting a cleaner, more sustainable energy future.", "EQT": "EQT Corporation is a leading independent natural gas production company in the United States, primarily focused on the Appalachian region. The company operates through its subsidiaries, EQT Production and EQT Midstream Partners, to explore, produce, and transport natural gas. EQT plays a significant role in meeting the country's growing energy demands, with a strong presence in the domestic natural gas market.", "XYZ": "Block, Inc. is a technology company that operates a suite of consumer and commercial payment products and services, including Cash App, a peer-to-peer payment platform, and Square, a point-of-sale and online payment processing system. The company's products enable individuals and businesses to manage their finances, accept payments, and access financial services. As a leading player in the digital payments space, Block, Inc. plays a significant role in shaping the future of money and commerce.", "WEC": "WEC Energy Group is a diversified energy company that generates and distributes electricity and natural gas to residential, commercial, and industrial customers in the Midwest and Great Plains regions. The company's key products and services include electricity and natural gas distribution, generation, and transmission, as well as energy storage and renewable energy solutions. As a leading utility company in the United States, WEC Energy Group plays a critical role in powering homes, businesses, and communities across its service area.", "ROP": "Roper Technologies is a diversified technology company that designs and manufactures engineered products and solutions for various industries, including medical, energy, and industrial markets. The company's portfolio includes medical imaging and diagnostics, radio frequency identification (RFID), and industrial automation products and services. Roper Technologies' innovative solutions enable customers to improve efficiency, productivity, and safety, driving growth and profitability in their respective markets.", "LVS": "Las Vegas Sands is a multinational resort and casino company that develops, owns, and operates integrated resorts in Asia, the United States, and Europe, offering a range of amenities and entertainment options. The company's key products and services include gaming, hospitality, and leisure activities, such as hotel rooms, dining, and entertainment venues. As a leading player in the global gaming industry, Las Vegas Sands provides a unique blend of entertainment, leisure, and economic development opportunities in the markets it operates in.", "IR": "Ingersoll Rand is a diversified industrial company that designs, manufactures, and sells industrial equipment, including air compressors, air treatment and gas systems, and power tools. The company's products and services are used in various industries such as construction, oil and gas, and mining, and are also used in the production of food and beverages, pharmaceuticals, and other consumer goods. Ingersoll Rand plays a critical role in the global economy by providing essential equipment and services that support the production and distribution of goods and services.", "CPRT": "Copart is a global online vehicle auction company that provides a platform for buyers and sellers to connect and conduct auctions for used and damaged vehicles. The company's services include online auctions, vehicle inspection reports, and transportation services, catering to a diverse range of customers including insurance companies, dealerships, and individual buyers. By providing a convenient and efficient platform for vehicle sales, Copart plays a significant role in the automotive industry, helping to manage inventory and facilitate the resale of vehicles.", "ARES": "Ares Management is a global alternative investment manager that provides a range of investment products and services to institutional investors, such as hedge funds, private equity funds, and credit strategies. The company offers a variety of investment solutions across multiple asset classes, including private equity, credit, and real estate. As a leading alternative investment manager, Ares Management plays a significant role in the global financial markets by providing investors with access to diverse and potentially high-return investment opportunities.", "RMD": "ResMed is a medical device company that develops, manufactures, and distributes medical equipment for the diagnosis, treatment, and management of sleep-related breathing disorders, as well as other respiratory diseases. The company's key products include sleep apnea and chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD) devices, such as continuous positive airway pressure (CPAP) machines and oxygen concentrators. ResMed's innovative solutions improve patient outcomes and quality of life, driving growth in the healthcare industry and enhancing the company's position as a leader in the medical device sector.", "LYV": "Live Nation Entertainment is a global entertainment company that promotes, produces, and hosts live music and other events, operating a network of venues, festivals, and ticketing platforms. The company's key products and services include ticketing, venue management, and event production, with a focus on live music experiences. As a leading player in the live entertainment industry, Live Nation Entertainment provides a platform for artists to connect with fans and for consumers to access a wide range of live events.", "GEHC": "GE HealthCare is a leading global health care company that provides medical imaging, diagnostics, patient care, and medical research technologies. The company offers a range of products and services, including MRI and CT scanners, ultrasound systems, and patient monitoring solutions, as well as informatics and analytics tools. By advancing health care technology, GE HealthCare enables healthcare providers to make more informed decisions and improve patient outcomes.", "KMB": "Kimberly-Clark is a multinational consumer goods corporation that develops and manufactures personal care and consumer tissue products. The company's key brands include Huggies diapers, Pull-Ups training pants, Depend adult incontinence products, Kleenex facial tissues, and Scott paper products, among others. As a leading provider of essential household and personal care items, Kimberly-Clark plays a significant role in the daily lives of consumers worldwide.", "ACGL": "Arch Capital Group Ltd is a global insurance company that provides property, casualty, and mortgage insurance and reinsurance products to clients worldwide. The company's key products include commercial and specialty insurance, reinsurance, and mortgage insurance, catering to a diverse range of industries and risk profiles. As a leading player in the global insurance market, Arch Capital Group plays a significant role in managing risk and providing financial protection to businesses and individuals.", "OTIS": "Otis Worldwide Corporation is a leading global manufacturer and maintainer of people-moving products, including elevators, escalators, moving walkways, and related services. The company's products are used in commercial and residential buildings, as well as in transportation and infrastructure applications, serving a wide range of industries and customers. As a key player in the global building infrastructure market, Otis Worldwide plays a critical role in enabling safe and efficient movement of people and goods.", "KVUE": "Kenvue is a multinational consumer healthcare company that develops, manufactures, and markets a range of consumer health products, including pain relief, respiratory, and gastrointestinal medications, as well as feminine care and baby care products. The company's portfolio includes well-known brands such as Tylenol, Neutrogena, and Aquafresh. As a leading player in the consumer staples sector, Kenvue provides essential products that improve the health and well-being of people around the world.", "STT": "State Street Corporation is a financial services and investment management company that provides a range of products and services to institutional investors, financial institutions, and individuals, including custody, investment management, and investment research. The company offers a variety of key products and services, including index funds, exchange-traded funds (ETFs), and alternative investments. As one of the largest custodian banks in the world, State Street plays a critical role in the global financial system by providing secure and efficient management of financial assets.", "TPL": "Texas Pacific Land Corporation is a leading landowner and real estate investment trust (REIT) focused on the acquisition, development, and sale of land in the Permian Basin of West Texas. The company primarily engages in the sale of land to oil and gas operators, providing a critical component of the upstream energy supply chain. As a key player in the Permian Basin, TPL plays a vital role in supporting the growth and development of the US oil and gas industry.", "WDAY": "Workday, Inc. is a cloud-based financial management and human capital management software provider that offers a range of enterprise software solutions to help organizations manage their financial, human capital, and planning processes. The company's key products include Workday Financial Management, Workday Human Capital Management, and Workday Planning, which enable businesses to streamline their operations, improve decision-making, and enhance employee engagement. Workday's solutions are used by over 5,000 organizations worldwide, making it a leading player in the cloud-based enterprise software market.", "PRU": "Prudential Financial is a multinational financial services company that provides a range of products and services, including life insurance, annuities, retirement-related services, mutual funds, and investment management. The company's key offerings include individual and group life insurance, group insurance, retirement services, and investment management solutions for institutional and individual clients. As one of the largest life insurers in the United States, Prudential Financial plays a significant role in helping individuals and businesses manage risk and achieve long-term financial goals.", "HBAN": "Huntington Bancshares is a bank holding company that provides a range of financial services, including consumer and commercial banking, through its subsidiary, The Huntington National Bank. The company offers deposit and loan products, payment solutions, and investment services to individuals, businesses, and corporations. As one of the largest banks in the Midwest, Huntington Bancshares plays a significant role in supporting local economic growth and development.", "MTB": "M&T Bank is a financial holding company that provides commercial and retail banking services to individuals, businesses, and institutions through its network of branches and ATMs. The company offers a range of products and services, including deposit accounts, credit cards, mortgages, commercial lending, and wealth management solutions. As one of the largest regional banks in the United States, M&T Bank plays a significant role in supporting economic growth and financial stability in the communities it serves.", "EXR": "Extra Space Storage is a self-storage company that owns and operates over 2,500 storage facilities across the United States. The company provides a range of storage solutions, including climate-controlled and drive-up access units, as well as ancillary services such as moving supplies and truck rentals. As a leading provider of self-storage services, Extra Space Storage plays a critical role in supporting the needs of individuals and businesses requiring temporary or long-term storage solutions.", "A": "Agilent Technologies is a leading provider of life sciences, diagnostics, and applied chemical markets, offering a range of products and services including analytical instruments, software, consumables, and application expertise. The company's solutions are used in various fields such as pharmaceuticals, biotechnology, food safety, and clinical diagnostics, enabling customers to advance their research, development, and healthcare applications. By providing innovative technologies and solutions, Agilent Technologies helps drive scientific discovery, improve healthcare outcomes, and enhance quality of life.", "FISV": "Fiserv is a leading global provider of financial services technology solutions, offering a range of products and services that enable financial institutions, businesses, and consumers to manage and process financial transactions. Its key offerings include payment processing, digital banking, and merchant acquiring solutions, as well as risk management and analytics tools. As a key player in the financial technology space, Fiserv plays a critical role in facilitating secure and efficient financial transactions, supporting the growth and development of the global economy.", "PAYX": "Paychex is a provider of integrated human capital management solutions for payroll, human resources, and benefits administration. The company offers a range of products and services, including payroll processing, time and attendance tracking, and benefits administration, to help businesses manage their workforce and comply with regulatory requirements. As a leading provider of human capital management solutions, Paychex helps businesses streamline their operations and improve their bottom line.", "ADM": "Archer Daniels Midland Company is a global food processing and commodities trading company that converts oilseeds, grains, and other agricultural commodities into a wide range of products, including food ingredients, animal feed, and biofuels. The company's key products include corn, soybean, and wheat-based products, as well as vegetable oils and sweeteners. As a leading player in the global food and feed industry, ADM plays a critical role in meeting the world's growing demand for food, feed, and fuel.", "UAL": "United Airlines Holdings is a major American airline holding company that operates a network of domestic and international scheduled airline services. The company's key products and services include passenger and cargo transportation, as well as loyalty programs and travel-related services. As one of the world's largest airlines, United Airlines Holdings plays a significant role in connecting people and businesses across the globe, driving economic growth and facilitating global trade.", "FICO": "Fair Isaac Corporation, operating under the ticker FICO, is a leading provider of analytics and decision management technology solutions. The company's key products and services include credit scoring models, fraud detection software, and customer management systems, which help businesses and financial institutions make informed decisions. By providing data-driven insights, FICO enables its clients to optimize their operations, reduce risk, and improve customer experiences, ultimately driving growth and profitability.", "EME": "Emcor Group, Inc. is a leading provider of mechanical and electrical construction and services, offering a range of solutions including construction, services, and industrial services to various industries. The company's key products and services include electrical and mechanical construction, building services, and industrial services, among others. Emcor's expertise and capabilities make it a significant player in the construction and services sector, serving a diverse range of clients across various markets.", "TDY": "Teledyne Technologies is a leading provider of advanced technologies, engineering solutions, and systems integration services to a diverse range of industries, including aerospace and defense, oil and gas, and marine. The company's key products and services include navigation and control systems, communication systems, and sensors, as well as commercial and military aircraft and space systems. Through its innovative solutions, Teledyne Technologies enables customers to improve performance, efficiency, and safety in their operations, driving growth and competitiveness in their respective markets.", "VICI": "Vici Properties is a real estate investment trust that specializes in acquiring and leasing properties to media, entertainment, and gaming companies. Its key assets include iconic venues such as sports stadiums, arenas, and theaters, providing a unique platform for content creation and distribution. By owning and leasing these properties, Vici Properties enables its tenants to focus on their core businesses while generating stable returns for its shareholders.", "IRM": "Iron Mountain Incorporated is a global leader in storage and information management services, providing secure and compliant storage solutions for paper, digital, and physical assets. The company's key products and services include data center and cloud storage, document management, and secure shredding and destruction, catering to a wide range of industries including healthcare, finance, and government. By safeguarding sensitive information and preserving physical assets, Iron Mountain plays a critical role in protecting its clients' data and intellectual property.", "CBOE": "Cboe Global Markets is a leading provider of marketplaces for buying and selling securities, derivatives, and other financial instruments. The company operates multiple exchanges, including the Cboe Options Exchange, Cboe Futures Exchange, and Cboe BZX Exchange, offering a range of products and services such as options trading, futures trading, and ETF listing. As a major player in the global financial markets, Cboe Global Markets plays a critical role in facilitating price discovery, liquidity, and risk management for investors and institutions.", "TPR": "Tapestry, Inc. is a global house of fashion brands that designs, manufactures, and distributes a wide range of luxury and lifestyle products. The company's portfolio includes Coach, Kate Spade New York, and Stuart Weitzman, offering high-quality handbags, wallets, shoes, and other accessories. As a leading player in the global fashion industry, Tapestry, Inc. matters for its ability to drive consumer trends and deliver consistent growth through its iconic brands and strategic brand investments.", "AEE": "Ameren is a diversified energy company that generates, transmits, and distributes electricity to approximately 2.4 million customers in Missouri and Illinois. The company's key products and services include electricity generation from coal, natural gas, and renewable sources, as well as natural gas distribution and transmission. As a major player in the U.S. utilities sector, Ameren plays a critical role in meeting the energy needs of its customers and supporting economic growth in the regions it serves.", "XYL": "Xylem Inc. is a leading global water technology company that designs, manufactures, and services equipment and systems for water and wastewater applications. The company's portfolio includes a range of products and services, including pumps, valves, and treatment systems, as well as software and analytics solutions for water management. By providing innovative solutions for water conservation and sustainability, Xylem plays a critical role in addressing global water challenges and supporting the health and well-being of communities worldwide.", "ATO": "Atmos Energy is a leading natural gas distributor in the United States, providing safe and reliable natural gas delivery services to over 3 million residential, commercial, and industrial customers across eight states. The company's key products and services include natural gas distribution, transmission, and storage, as well as infrastructure development and maintenance. As a critical component of the nation's energy infrastructure, Atmos Energy plays a vital role in supporting economic growth, energy security, and environmental sustainability.", "DTE": "DTE Energy is a diversified energy company that provides a range of energy-related services, including the generation, transmission, distribution, and sale of electricity and natural gas to residential, commercial, and industrial customers in Michigan. The company's key products and services include electricity, natural gas, and energy-related services such as energy efficiency and renewable energy solutions. As a leading energy provider in the Midwest, DTE Energy plays a critical role in meeting the region's energy needs and supporting economic growth and development.", "HAL": "Halliburton Company is a leading provider of services and products to the energy industry, offering a range of solutions including drilling and production, completion and production, and pipeline and processing services. The company's key products and services include drilling fluids, cementing, and completion and production tools, as well as digital solutions for the energy industry. As a major player in the energy sector, Halliburton plays a critical role in meeting the world's growing demand for energy.", "RJF": "Raymond James Financial is a diversified financial services company that provides wealth management, capital markets, asset management, and banking services to individuals, corporations, and municipalities. The company offers a range of products and services, including brokerage and investment advisory services, investment banking, and asset management solutions. As a leading independent financial services company, Raymond James Financial plays a significant role in the financial industry by providing comprehensive financial solutions to its clients.", "DOV": "Dover Corporation is a diversified global industrial company that operates through various segments, including Engineered Systems, Clean Energy & Fueling, Imaging & Identification, Pumps & Instruments, and Fluids. Dover's portfolio includes a range of products and services, including pumps, compressors, fluid management equipment, and imaging and identification solutions. The company's diverse offerings enable customers across various industries to improve efficiency, productivity, and safety, making it a significant player in the global industrial landscape.", "CTSH": "Cognizant is a leading global professional services company that provides a wide range of information technology, consulting, and business process services, including digital transformation, cloud, artificial intelligence, and cybersecurity solutions. The company's services help clients across various industries to improve their operational efficiency, enhance customer experience, and drive innovation. As a key player in the digital transformation space, Cognizant enables businesses to stay competitive in a rapidly changing market.", "WAT": "Waters Corporation is a global leader in analytical instrumentation and laboratory software, providing innovative solutions for life sciences, environmental, food safety, and industrial markets. The company's products include chromatography systems, mass spectrometry systems, thermal analysis systems, and laboratory software, enabling customers to analyze and understand complex biological and chemical samples. By advancing analytical science, Waters Corporation helps researchers, scientists, and healthcare professionals make new discoveries and improve patient outcomes.", "ULTA": "Ulta Beauty is a leading beauty retailer that offers a wide range of products from over 500 brands, including its own in-house labels, as well as salon services such as hair cutting, coloring, and styling. The company operates a chain of stores across the United States and also provides e-commerce services, making it a one-stop-shop for beauty enthusiasts. As a major player in the beauty industry, Ulta Beauty matters to consumers and investors alike due to its strong brand portfolio, loyalty program, and growing online presence.", "IQV": "IQVIA is a leading global provider of advanced analytics, technology solutions, and clinical research services to the healthcare industry. The company offers a range of products and services, including data analytics, clinical trial management, and medical communication solutions, to help pharmaceutical, biotech, and medical device companies navigate the complex healthcare landscape. By providing insights and solutions to improve patient outcomes and reduce healthcare costs, IQVIA plays a critical role in shaping the future of healthcare.", "FE": "FirstEnergy is a diversified energy company that generates, transmits, and distributes electricity to approximately 6 million customers in the Midwest and Mid-Atlantic regions. The company operates a portfolio of power plants, including nuclear, coal, and natural gas facilities, as well as a network of transmission and distribution lines. As a major player in the US energy sector, FirstEnergy plays a critical role in meeting the country's growing electricity demands.", "CHTR": "Charter Communications is a leading provider of cable television, high-speed internet, and telephone services in the United States. The company offers a range of products and services, including Spectrum TV, Spectrum Internet, and Spectrum Voice, to residential and commercial customers. As a major player in the US broadband market, Charter Communications plays a critical role in connecting millions of households and businesses to the digital economy.", "VRSK": "Verisk Analytics is a leading data analytics and risk assessment company that provides predictive analytics and decision support solutions to the insurance, energy, and financial services industries. The company's key products and services include data analytics, risk assessment, and decision support tools that help clients manage risk, improve profitability, and enhance customer experiences. By providing critical insights and predictive analytics, Verisk Analytics helps its clients make informed business decisions and stay ahead of emerging trends and risks.", "PPL": "PPL Corporation is a multinational utility company that generates, transmits, and distributes electricity to approximately 10 million customers in the United States, the United Kingdom, and Latin America. The company's key products and services include electricity generation, transmission, and distribution, as well as natural gas distribution. As a leading utility provider, PPL plays a critical role in meeting the energy needs of its customers and contributing to the stability of the global energy market.", "WTW": "Willis Towers Watson is a global advisory, broking, and solutions company that provides a range of services including risk management, investment, benefits, and talent management to clients across various industries. The company offers a suite of products and services, including actuarial and investment consulting, insurance brokerage, and human capital consulting, to help clients navigate complex business challenges. By providing expert guidance and innovative solutions, Willis Towers Watson helps clients make informed decisions and achieve their strategic objectives.", "ROL": "Rollins, Inc. is a holding company that provides pest and termite control services through its subsidiaries, including Orkin, HomeFree Pest Control, and other regional brands. The company offers a range of services, including residential and commercial pest control, termite protection, and wildlife control, leveraging its extensive network of branches and technicians. As a leading provider of pest control services, Rollins, Inc. plays a significant role in maintaining public health and safety.", "STLD": "Steel Dynamics is a leading domestic steel producer and metals recycling company. The company operates a portfolio of steel production facilities, steel finishing facilities, and metals recycling facilities, producing a range of steel products, including flat roll steel, long roll steel, and steel tubing. As a major player in the US steel industry, Steel Dynamics plays a critical role in supporting the country's infrastructure development and manufacturing sectors.", "HPE": "Hewlett Packard Enterprise is a multinational information technology company that designs, develops, and sells software, cloud computing, and data storage solutions to businesses and governments worldwide. The company's key products and services include servers, storage systems, networking equipment, and cybersecurity solutions, as well as software for artificial intelligence, machine learning, and the Internet of Things. As a leading provider of enterprise technology, HPE enables businesses to modernize their infrastructure, improve operational efficiency, and drive innovation in the digital age.", "KHC": "Kraft Heinz is a multinational food and beverage company that manufactures and distributes a wide range of consumer goods, including condiments, cheese, coffee, infant nutrition, and frozen foods. The company's portfolio includes iconic brands such as Kraft, Heinz, Oscar Mayer, and Planters. As one of the largest food companies in the world, Kraft Heinz plays a significant role in the global food industry, providing essential products to households and businesses worldwide.", "DXCM": "Dexcom is a medical technology company that designs, manufactures, and markets continuous glucose monitoring systems for people with diabetes. The company's key products include its G5 Mobile and G6 systems, which provide real-time glucose readings and alerts to help manage the condition. By offering accurate and user-friendly glucose monitoring solutions, Dexcom helps improve the lives of people with diabetes and enables them to make informed decisions about their health.", "EIX": "Edison International is a multinational energy holding company that generates and distributes electricity through its subsidiaries, including Southern California Edison. The company's key products and services include electricity generation, transmission, and distribution to residential, commercial, and industrial customers in Southern California. As one of the largest electric utilities in the United States, Edison International plays a critical role in meeting the region's energy needs and supporting economic growth.", "CNP": "CenterPoint Energy is a utility company that provides electric transmission and distribution services to residential, commercial, and industrial customers in the United States. The company operates in eight states, delivering electricity and natural gas to over 2.5 million metered customers. As a key player in the energy infrastructure sector, CenterPoint Energy plays a vital role in meeting the energy needs of its customers and supporting the nation's economic growth.", "ES": "Eversource Energy is a leading energy delivery company that provides electricity, natural gas, and water services to residential, commercial, and industrial customers in the United States. The company operates through three main segments: electric, gas, and water, offering essential energy and water services to over 4 million customers across Connecticut, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, and Rhode Island. As a critical component of the nation's energy infrastructure, Eversource Energy plays a vital role in powering homes, businesses, and communities across the Northeast region.", "JBL": "Jabil is a global manufacturing solutions company that designs and supplies a wide range of products and services to leading technology companies in the electronics, automotive, industrial, and healthcare industries. The company's portfolio includes contract manufacturing, design and development, supply chain management, and product design services, enabling its customers to bring innovative products to market quickly and efficiently. As a key partner to many leading technology companies, Jabil plays a critical role in the global supply chain, helping to drive innovation and growth in the industries it serves.", "DVN": "Devon Energy is an independent energy company that explores, develops, and produces oil, natural gas, and natural gas liquids in the United States and Canada. The company's operations primarily focus on onshore oil and natural gas production, with a presence in the Permian Basin, the Delaware Basin, and other key shale plays. As a leading producer of oil and natural gas, Devon Energy plays a significant role in meeting global energy demand.", "BIIB": "Biogen is a biotechnology company that develops, manufactures, and commercializes therapies for the treatment of neurological and autoimmune diseases. The company's key products include multiple sclerosis treatments such as Avonex, Tysabri, and Plegridy, as well as spinal muscular atrophy treatment Spinraza and Alzheimer's disease treatment Aduhelm. Biogen's innovative therapies have improved the lives of millions of patients worldwide, making it a leader in the healthcare industry.", "WRB": "W. R. Berkley Corporation is a holding company that engages in the operation of various insurance business units, offering a range of property and casualty insurance products and services to businesses and individuals. The company's key products include commercial insurance, specialty insurance, and reinsurance, as well as personal insurance lines. As a leading provider of insurance solutions, W. R. Berkley plays a significant role in managing risk and protecting assets for its clients.", "TSCO": "Tractor Supply Company is a retail chain that operates a chain of retail stores offering products and services for the rural lifestyle. The company provides a wide range of products including feed, animal health products, and pet food, as well as lawn and garden supplies, tools, and workwear. As a leading destination for rural enthusiasts and farmers, Tractor Supply Company serves a vital role in supporting the needs of the rural community.", "NTRS": "Northern Trust is a global financial institution providing asset servicing, fund administration, custody, and investment management services to institutional and individual clients. The company offers a range of products and services, including investment management, asset servicing, and banking solutions, to help clients achieve their financial goals. As a leading provider of financial services, Northern Trust plays a critical role in supporting the global economy and helping clients navigate complex financial markets.", "STZ": "Constellation Brands is a leading beverage alcohol company that produces, imports, and distributes beer, wine, and spirits in the United States, Canada, Mexico, and other international markets. The company's key brands include Corona Extra, Modelo Especial, and Svedka Vodka, among others. As a major player in the beverage alcohol industry, Constellation Brands plays a significant role in shaping consumer preferences and trends in the global market.", "LEN": "Lennar Corporation is a leading homebuilder and real estate developer in the United States, specializing in the construction and sale of single-family homes, condominiums, and apartment communities. The company operates in 21 states and Puerto Rico, offering a range of home designs and price points to meet diverse customer needs. As a major player in the US housing market, Lennar's performance is closely watched as an indicator of the broader housing sector and the overall health of the US economy.", "HUBB": "Hubbell Incorporated is a global supplier of electrical and utility infrastructure solutions, providing a wide range of products and services for the construction, industrial, and utility markets. The company's key products include electrical connectors, lighting and controls, and utility solutions, which are used in various applications such as commercial and industrial construction, renewable energy systems, and smart grid infrastructure. As a leading provider of critical infrastructure solutions, Hubbell Incorporated plays a vital role in supporting the growth and development of the global economy.", "MTD": "Mettler Toledo is a leading global provider of precision instruments and services for laboratory, industrial, and food retailing applications. The company offers a range of products including balances, scales, and analytical instruments, as well as services such as calibration and consulting. By providing accurate and reliable measurement solutions, Mettler Toledo enables its customers to improve product quality, efficiency, and safety.", "PPG": "PPG Industries is a multinational materials company that develops and delivers a range of coatings, specialty materials, and glass products for various industries, including aerospace, automotive, construction, and consumer electronics. The company's key products and services include paints, coatings, sealants, solar films, and architectural glass, among others. As a leading supplier of materials solutions, PPG Industries plays a critical role in enabling innovation and sustainability across multiple sectors.", "AWK": "American Water Works Company, Inc. is a holding company that provides water and wastewater services to approximately 15 million people in the United States and the United Kingdom. The company's key products and services include water and wastewater treatment, distribution, and collection, as well as stormwater management. As a leading provider of essential water infrastructure, American Water Works plays a critical role in ensuring public health and safety through reliable access to clean water and sanitation services.", "OMC": "Omnicom Group is a global advertising, marketing, and corporate communications holding company that provides a range of services including advertising, public relations, and digital marketing. The company operates through a network of agencies and brands, offering services such as creative, media planning, and customer relationship management. As one of the largest advertising and marketing companies in the world, Omnicom Group plays a significant role in shaping the global marketing landscape.", "ON": "ON Semiconductor designs, manufactures, and markets a broad portfolio of semiconductor components and solutions for the automotive, industrial, computing, and consumer electronics markets. The company's product offerings include power management, analog, timing, and discrete components, as well as system-on-chip (SoC) solutions. ON Semiconductor's products enable the development of more efficient, reliable, and connected electronic systems, driving innovation in various industries and applications.", "EXPE": "Expedia Group is a leading travel technology company that provides a platform for consumers to research, plan, book, and experience travel. The company's key products and services include Expedia.com, Hotels.com, and Orbitz, as well as its loyalty program, Expedia Rewards. By connecting travelers with a vast selection of travel options, Expedia Group enables individuals to explore the world and discover new experiences, driving growth in the global travel industry.", "CFG": "Citizens Financial Group is a bank holding company that provides a range of financial services to individuals, corporations, and other financial institutions through its retail banking and commercial banking segments. The company offers deposit and loan products, including checking and savings accounts, mortgages, and commercial loans, as well as investment and wealth management services. As a leading regional bank in the United States, Citizens Financial Group plays a significant role in supporting economic growth and financial stability in the communities it serves.", "FIS": "Fidelity National Information Services (FIS) is a leading provider of financial technology solutions, offering a range of products and services that enable financial institutions to process transactions, manage risk, and improve customer engagement. The company's key offerings include payment processing, banking and lending solutions, and risk and compliance management tools. As a key player in the financial technology sector, FIS helps facilitate secure and efficient financial transactions, supporting the growth and stability of the global economy.", "CINF": "Cincinnati Financial Corporation is a property casualty insurance holding company that provides commercial and personal insurance products through its subsidiaries, including The Cincinnati Insurance Company, Insurance Company of the Midwest, and other affiliates. The company offers a range of insurance products, including commercial property, casualty, and workers' compensation insurance, as well as personal auto, homeowners, and umbrella insurance. Cincinnati Financial's products and services help individuals and businesses manage risk and protect their assets.", "EXE": "Expand Energy is a leading provider of integrated energy solutions, offering a diverse portfolio of natural gas and oil production, midstream transportation, and downstream refining services. The company's key products and services include natural gas and oil exploration, production, and transportation, as well as refining and marketing of petroleum products. As a major player in the energy sector, Expand Energy plays a critical role in meeting the world's growing demand for energy, driving economic growth and development.", "Q": "Qnity Electronics is a leading provider of advanced semiconductor solutions, designing and manufacturing high-performance microprocessors, graphics processing units, and artificial intelligence accelerators. The company's products are used in a wide range of applications, including cloud computing, data centers, artificial intelligence, and autonomous vehicles. As a key player in the global semiconductor industry, Qnity Electronics plays a critical role in enabling the development of emerging technologies and driving innovation in the Information Technology sector.", "PHM": "PulteGroup is a leading American homebuilder and land developer, operating in the United States and Canada. The company designs, builds, and sells new homes in over 40 markets across the country, offering a range of housing options from entry-level to luxury, through its brands Pulte Homes, Del Webb, and DiVosta. As a major player in the US housing market, PulteGroup's performance provides insight into the country's housing demand and economic health.", "EFX": "Equifax is a global information solutions company that provides consumer and commercial data, analytics, and technology to businesses, governments, and individuals. Its key products and services include credit reporting, identity verification, and fraud prevention solutions. By providing critical insights and decision-making tools, Equifax helps its clients navigate complex data-driven environments and mitigate risk, making it a vital player in the global economy.", "AVB": "AvalonBay Communities is a real estate investment trust (REIT) that develops, owns, and operates high-quality apartment communities in the United States. The company focuses on providing upscale multifamily housing options in desirable locations, with a portfolio of properties in the Northeast, Mid-Atlantic, and West Coast regions. AvalonBay Communities plays a significant role in the US housing market, offering a stable source of income for investors and providing quality living spaces for residents.", "CHD": "Church & Dwight Co., Inc. is a consumer goods company that manufactures and markets a wide range of household, personal care, and specialty products. The company's portfolio includes well-known brands such as Arm & Hammer, OxiClean, and Trojan, among others. As a leading player in the consumer staples sector, Church & Dwight's products are staples in many households, providing essential cleaning, personal care, and hygiene solutions.", "LUV": "Southwest Airlines is a major United States-based low-cost carrier that operates a network of domestic and international scheduled air transportation services. The company's key products include scheduled air transportation, cargo services, and aircraft leasing. As one of the largest airlines in the world, Southwest Airlines plays a significant role in connecting people and businesses across the globe, driving economic growth and development.", "SYF": "Synchrony Financial is a consumer financial services company that provides a range of credit products and services to consumers, including credit cards, retail financing, and consumer financing. The company offers a variety of key products and services, including private label credit cards, installment loans, and deposit products. As a leading consumer finance company, Synchrony Financial plays a significant role in the US financial services industry, serving millions of customers across various sectors.", "EQR": "Equity Residential is a real estate investment trust (REIT) that owns, operates, and develops multifamily properties, primarily in the United States. The company's portfolio includes approximately 309 properties containing over 79,000 apartment units across 17 states and the District of Columbia, providing housing options for residents and generating rental income. As a leading multifamily REIT, Equity Residential plays a significant role in the US housing market, offering stable income and long-term growth opportunities for investors.", "DLTR": "Dollar Tree operates a chain of variety stores offering a range of products at fixed prices of $1 or less, including household essentials, food, personal care items, and seasonal merchandise. The company's stores are located throughout the United States and Canada, providing affordable shopping options to budget-conscious consumers. As a leading dollar store retailer, Dollar Tree plays a significant role in the discount retail market, catering to customers seeking value and convenience.", "RF": "Regions Financial Corporation is a bank holding company that provides a range of consumer and commercial banking services through its subsidiary, Regions Bank. The company offers a variety of financial products and services, including deposit accounts, loans, credit cards, and investment services. As one of the largest banks in the United States, Regions Financial plays a significant role in the country's financial infrastructure, serving millions of customers across the southeastern and midwestern regions.", "DRI": "Darden Restaurants is a leading operator of casual dining restaurants in the United States, owning and franchising a diverse portfolio of brands including Olive Garden, LongHorn Steakhouse, and Cheddar's Scratch Kitchen. The company's restaurants offer a range of menu options, from Italian and American comfort food to steakhouses and casual family dining. As a prominent player in the casual dining industry, Darden Restaurants provides a convenient and affordable dining experience for millions of customers across the country.", "SW": "Smurfit Kappa Group, trading as Smurfit Westrock on the NYSE under the ticker SW, is a multinational packaging company that manufactures and supplies paper-based packaging solutions, including corrugated containers, solid board, and other packaging materials. The company serves various industries, including food and beverage, e-commerce, and retail, providing innovative packaging solutions to meet the evolving needs of its customers. As a leading player in the packaging industry, Smurfit Westrock plays a critical role in reducing waste and promoting sustainable packaging practices.", "BRO": "Brown & Brown is a leading insurance brokerage firm that provides risk management solutions and insurance products to businesses and individuals. The company offers a range of services, including property and casualty insurance, employee benefits, and surety and fidelity insurance, through its network of agents and brokers. By helping clients manage risk and navigate complex insurance markets, Brown & Brown plays a critical role in supporting the stability and growth of the global economy.", "STE": "Steris is a global leader in infection prevention and surgical solutions, providing a comprehensive range of products and services that support healthcare facilities in maintaining a safe and sterile environment. The company's key offerings include sterilization and disinfection systems, surgical instrument processing equipment, and infection prevention solutions, among others. By helping to prevent hospital-acquired infections and improve surgical outcomes, Steris plays a critical role in enhancing patient safety and quality of care.", "FOX": "Fox Corporation is a diversified media and entertainment company that operates a portfolio of cable television networks and news brands, including Fox News, Fox Business, and Fox Sports. The company's key products and services include news, sports, and entertainment programming, as well as digital media and advertising solutions. As a leading media conglomerate, Fox Corporation plays a significant role in shaping public discourse and providing entertainment to millions of viewers worldwide.", "WSM": "Williams-Sonoma, Inc. operates as a multi-brand specialty retailer of home furnishings and cooking-related products. The company offers a portfolio of brands, including Williams-Sonoma, Pottery Barn, West Elm, and Rejuvenation, which provide high-quality products for the home. As a leading player in the home furnishings market, Williams-Sonoma, Inc. matters to consumers seeking stylish and functional products for their living spaces.", "VLTO": "Veralto is a leading provider of industrial automation and control solutions, offering a range of products and services including programmable logic controllers, human-machine interfaces, and industrial communication systems. The company's products enable customers to improve efficiency, productivity, and safety in various industries such as manufacturing, oil and gas, and power generation. As a key player in the industrial automation market, Veralto plays a critical role in driving innovation and digital transformation in the global industrial sector.", "CTRA": "Coterra Energy, Inc. is a leading independent oil and natural gas producer in the United States, primarily focused on the exploration, development, and production of oil and natural gas properties in the Permian Basin and other key shale plays. The company operates a diverse portfolio of assets, including oil and natural gas wells, pipelines, and midstream infrastructure, enabling it to efficiently develop and transport its hydrocarbon resources. As a major player in the US energy sector, Coterra Energy plays a critical role in meeting domestic energy demand and contributing to the country's energy security.", "GIS": "General Mills is a multinational food company that develops, manufactures, markets, and sells consumer foods worldwide. The company's portfolio includes well-known brands such as Cheerios, Betty Crocker, Pillsbury, and Yoplait, among others, offering a range of products including cereals, baking products, and frozen meals. As a leading player in the global food industry, General Mills matters for its significant presence in the consumer staples sector and its commitment to delivering high-quality, convenient food options to consumers worldwide.", "FOXA": "Fox Corporation is a diversified media company that operates a portfolio of cable television networks, including Fox News, Fox Business, Fox Sports, and the Fox broadcast network. The company's key products and services include news, sports, and entertainment programming, as well as digital media platforms. As a leading provider of news and entertainment content, Fox Corporation plays a significant role in shaping the national conversation and influencing popular culture.", "CMS": "CMS Energy is a diversified energy company that generates, transmits, and distributes electricity and natural gas to residential, commercial, and industrial customers in Michigan. The company's key products and services include electricity and natural gas supply, transmission and distribution, and energy storage solutions. As a leading utility provider in the Midwest, CMS Energy plays a critical role in meeting the region's energy needs and contributing to a reliable and sustainable energy infrastructure.", "LH": "Labcorp is a leading global life sciences company that provides clinical laboratory services, genomic testing, and medical diagnostics to healthcare professionals, pharmaceutical companies, and patients. The company's comprehensive range of testing services includes genetic testing, infectious disease testing, and cancer diagnostics, among others. By providing critical diagnostic information, Labcorp helps healthcare professionals make informed decisions, improve patient outcomes, and advance medical research.", "DGX": "Quest Diagnostics is a leading healthcare information and services company that provides diagnostic testing, information, and services to patients, physicians, hospitals, and health plans. The company offers a range of diagnostic tests, including clinical laboratory tests, genomic testing, and information technology solutions, to help healthcare providers diagnose and treat diseases. By providing critical diagnostic insights, Quest Diagnostics plays a vital role in improving patient outcomes and advancing healthcare quality.", "BG": "Bunge Global is a leading agribusiness and food company that sources, processes, and distributes food and feed ingredients globally. The company's key products and services include oilseed processing, grains and oilseeds trading, and edible oil refining, as well as sugar, bioenergy, and fertilizers. As a major player in the global food supply chain, Bunge Global plays a critical role in ensuring food security and stability for consumers worldwide.", "CPAY": "Corpay is a financial technology company that provides a suite of payment and cash management solutions to businesses, enabling them to streamline their payment processes and improve their working capital. The company's key products and services include payment automation, accounts payable and accounts receivable automation, and cash flow management. By simplifying payment operations, Corpay helps businesses reduce costs, increase efficiency, and gain better control over their financial resources.", "KEY": "KeyCorp is a bank holding company that provides a range of banking services to consumers and businesses through its subsidiary KeyBank National Association. KeyBank offers personal and commercial banking, investment and wealth management, and insurance services, as well as mortgage and consumer finance products. As one of the largest bank holding companies in the United States, KeyCorp plays a significant role in the country's financial system.", "L": "Loews Corporation is a multinational conglomerate holding company that operates through several business segments, including Loews Hotels, CNA Financial, Diamond Offshore Drilling, Boardwalk Pipeline Partners, and Loews Minerals Management. The company's key products and services include hotel operations, property and casualty insurance, offshore drilling services, and pipeline transportation. As a diversified conglomerate, Loews Corporation provides a unique combination of financial and operational expertise to its various business segments.", "NI": "NiSource is a diversified energy holding company that operates through its subsidiaries, providing natural gas and electric services to approximately 3.5 million customers across seven states in the U.S. The company's key products and services include natural gas distribution, transmission, and storage, as well as electric distribution and transmission. As a major player in the U.S. utilities sector, NiSource plays a vital role in meeting the energy needs of its customers and supporting the country's energy infrastructure.", "TSN": "Tyson Foods, Inc. is a multinational food company that processes and distributes a range of protein-based products, including chicken, beef, pork, and prepared foods. The company's portfolio includes brands such as Tyson, Jimmy Dean, Hillshire Farm, and Ball Park, among others. As a leading player in the global meat industry, Tyson Foods plays a significant role in meeting the world's growing demand for protein-rich foods.", "LDOS": "Leidos is a leading provider of defense, intelligence, and civil solutions, offering a range of services and products in areas such as cybersecurity, data analytics, and engineering. The company's key offerings include IT services, engineering and technical services, and national security solutions, supporting government agencies and commercial clients. As a major player in the defense and aerospace industries, Leidos plays a critical role in advancing national security and driving innovation.", "CHRW": "C.H. Robinson is a global logistics and transportation company that provides a range of supply chain solutions to its customers, including freight brokerage, transportation management, and warehousing services. The company connects shippers with carriers through its network of over 300 offices worldwide, facilitating the movement of goods across various industries. By streamlining the logistics process, C.H. Robinson helps its customers reduce costs, improve efficiency, and enhance their overall supply chain resilience.", "IP": "International Paper is a global producer of pulp, paper, packaging, and cellulose fibers, offering a range of products including printing papers, packaging materials, and tissue products. The company serves various end-markets, including packaging, consumer products, and industrial applications, providing essential materials for a wide range of industries. As a leading manufacturer of paper and packaging products, International Paper plays a critical role in facilitating global commerce and connectivity.", "HUM": "Humana is a health care company that offers a range of products and services, including Medicare Advantage and commercial health insurance, as well as health and wellness services. The company's key products and services include pharmacy benefit management, care coordination, and health information technology solutions. As one of the largest health insurance companies in the United States, Humana plays a significant role in providing access to healthcare for millions of Americans.", "AMCR": "Amcor is a global leader in the design and manufacture of packaging products for the food, beverage, pharmaceutical, and medical industries. The company's product portfolio includes flexible and rigid plastic packaging, glass and metal containers, and specialty cartons, serving a diverse range of customers worldwide. As a key player in the packaging industry, Amcor plays a critical role in ensuring the safety, quality, and sustainability of packaged goods.", "JBHT": "J.B. Hunt Transport Services, Inc. is a leading global logistics company that provides a range of transportation and supply chain services, including intermodal, truckload, less-than-truckload, dedicated, refrigerated, and supply chain services. The company operates a large fleet of trucks, intermodal containers, and trailers, and manages a network of terminals and logistics facilities across North America. As a major player in the logistics industry, J.B. Hunt plays a critical role in facilitating the movement of goods and supplies across the supply chain.", "CNC": "Centene Corporation is a healthcare company that provides a range of services, including health insurance, pharmacy benefits management, and specialty pharmacy services, primarily to low-income and underinsured individuals. The company operates through its subsidiaries, Ambetter and Fidelis Care, offering Medicaid, Medicare, and the Health Insurance Marketplace plans. As a leading provider of managed care services, Centene plays a critical role in expanding access to healthcare for vulnerable populations.", "BR": "Broadridge Financial Solutions is a technology-enabled financial services company providing communications, technology, and data and analytics solutions to the financial services industry. Its key products and services include investor communication and proxy solicitation, data and analytics, and securities processing and clearing. By enabling the secure and efficient exchange of information, Broadridge plays a critical role in facilitating the operations of the financial services industry.", "GPN": "Global Payments is a leading provider of payment technology and software solutions, offering a range of products and services that enable businesses to accept and process payments across various channels. The company's key offerings include payment processing, point-of-sale solutions, and digital payment services, which cater to merchants, financial institutions, and consumers worldwide. As a leading player in the payments industry, Global Payments plays a critical role in facilitating global commerce and enabling businesses to thrive in a rapidly evolving digital landscape.", "SBAC": "SBA Communications is a real estate investment trust (REIT) that specializes in the ownership and operation of wireless communication infrastructure in the United States, Canada, and other countries. The company owns and operates over 42,000 cell towers and other wireless communication sites, providing critical infrastructure for wireless carriers and other tenants. By owning and operating these sites, SBA Communications enables wireless carriers to expand their network coverage and capacity, driving growth in the wireless industry.", "RL": "Ralph Lauren Corporation designs, manufactures, and markets lifestyle products, including clothing, accessories, home furnishings, and fragrances, under the Ralph Lauren, Polo, and other brands. The company's products are sold through a network of retail stores, e-commerce sites, and third-party wholesale customers worldwide. As a leading global luxury lifestyle brand, Ralph Lauren Corporation offers high-quality, stylish products that cater to consumers seeking premium fashion and lifestyle experiences.", "FSLR": "First Solar is a leading global provider of photovoltaic (PV) solar energy solutions, offering a range of products and services including thin-film solar panels and solar power plant development and construction. The company's innovative technology enables the efficient and cost-effective generation of clean energy, contributing to the global transition to renewable energy sources. As a pioneer in the solar industry, First Solar plays a critical role in reducing greenhouse gas emissions and promoting sustainable energy solutions.", "ALB": "Albemarle Corporation is a global leader in the development, manufacture, and supply of lithium and other specialty chemicals for a range of industries, including energy storage, consumer electronics, and automotive. The company's key products include lithium compounds, bromine, and other specialty chemicals used in lithium-ion batteries, pharmaceuticals, and other applications. As a critical supplier to the growing electric vehicle and renewable energy markets, Albemarle plays a vital role in enabling the transition to a more sustainable energy future.", "PFG": "Principal Financial Group is a global financial services company that offers a range of products and services, including retirement and income solutions, life and health insurance, and asset management. The company's key products include group and individual life insurance, variable and fixed annuities, and retirement plans. As one of the largest insurance companies in the US, Principal Financial Group plays a significant role in helping individuals and businesses achieve their financial goals and secure their financial futures.", "VRSN": "Verisign is a global leader in domain name registration services, providing a range of products and services that enable the operation of the internet's core infrastructure. The company's key offerings include domain name registration, DNS (Domain Name System) services, and cybersecurity solutions, which help protect online identities and transactions. As a critical component of the internet's backbone, Verisign plays a vital role in ensuring the stability and security of online communications.", "NVR": "NVR, Inc. is a homebuilding and mortgage finance company that designs, constructs, and sells single-family and multi-family homes, as well as commercial buildings. The company's key products and services include homebuilding, mortgage financing, and land development. NVR operates through its subsidiaries, including Ryan Homes, NVHomes, Rymar Homes, Fox Ridge Homes, and others, and is a leading player in the US homebuilding industry.", "LULU": "Lululemon Athletica is a Canadian athletic apparel company that designs, manufactures, and distributes high-performance yoga pants, tops, and other athletic apparel for men and women. The company's products are known for their technical fabrics, comfortable fits, and stylish designs, appealing to consumers seeking premium athletic wear for yoga, running, and other fitness activities. As a leading brand in the athleisure market, Lululemon Athletica has become a staple in the lives of many health-conscious consumers, driving growth in the global athletic apparel industry.", "PKG": "Packaging Corporation of America is a leading manufacturer of containerboard and corrugated packaging products, offering a range of packaging solutions for various industries. The company's key products include containerboard, corrugated packaging, and specialty packaging products, serving customers across the food, beverage, and consumer goods sectors. As a leading player in the packaging industry, PCA plays a critical role in facilitating the efficient transportation and storage of goods, supporting the growth of e-commerce and other industries.", "DD": "DuPont is a multinational corporation that develops and manufactures a range of materials and products, including chemicals, materials science, and agriculture solutions. The company's key products include Kevlar, Tyvek, and Sorona, as well as crop protection and seeds. As a leading materials science company, DuPont plays a crucial role in driving innovation and sustainability across various industries.", "TROW": "T. Rowe Price is a global investment management firm that provides a range of financial products and services to individual and institutional investors, including mutual funds, exchange-traded funds, and retirement plans. The company offers a diverse portfolio of actively managed investment strategies across various asset classes, sectors, and geographic regions. As a leading investment manager, T. Rowe Price helps clients achieve their long-term financial goals through its expertise and research-driven investment approach.", "IFF": "International Flavors & Fragrances is a global leader in the creation of flavors and fragrances for the food, beverage, personal care, and household products industries. The company develops and manufactures a diverse portfolio of products, including fragrances, flavor ingredients, and functional ingredients, which are used by leading consumer goods companies worldwide. As a key supplier of ingredients to the global food, beverage, and personal care industries, IFF plays a critical role in shaping consumer preferences and driving innovation in these sectors.", "SNA": "Snap-on Incorporated is a leading global innovator, designer, manufacturer, and distributor of tools, diagnostics, equipment, and software for professional mechanics and technicians. The company's product portfolio includes hand tools, power tools, diagnostic software, and equipment for automotive repair and maintenance, as well as other industries such as aerospace, agriculture, and construction. Snap-on's products and services enable professionals to work more efficiently and effectively, driving productivity and customer satisfaction in the industries they serve.", "NTAP": "NetApp is a global leader in cloud data services, providing software, systems, and services to help organizations manage and store their data efficiently. The company's key products and services include its ONTAP operating system, storage systems, and cloud data services, which enable businesses to simplify their data management and accelerate their digital transformation. By providing a unified platform for data management, NetApp helps organizations to improve their agility, reduce costs, and enhance their overall data-driven decision-making capabilities.", "EXPD": "Expeditors International is a global logistics and freight forwarding company that provides customized supply chain solutions to a diverse base of customers. The company's key services include air and ocean freight forwarding, customs brokerage, warehousing and distribution, and supply chain consulting. Expeditors International plays a critical role in facilitating the movement of goods across the globe, connecting buyers and sellers in a rapidly changing and increasingly complex global marketplace.", "INCY": "Incyte is a biopharmaceutical company focused on the discovery, development, and commercialization of innovative medicines to address serious medical conditions. The company's key products include Jakafi, a treatment for myelofibrosis and polycythemia vera, and Pemazyre, a treatment for cholangiocarcinoma. Incyte's research and development efforts aim to improve patient outcomes and quality of life in various therapeutic areas, including oncology and immunology.", "ZBH": "Zimmer Biomet is a global leader in musculoskeletal healthcare, providing a comprehensive portfolio of orthopedic reconstructive products, spine and sports medicine solutions, and dental implants. The company's product offerings include knee and hip replacement systems, spinal implants, and dental reconstruction systems, among others. As a leading innovator in the orthopedic and dental industries, Zimmer Biomet plays a critical role in improving patient outcomes and enhancing the quality of life for millions of people worldwide.", "LII": "Lennox International is a global leader in the design, manufacture, and marketing of climate control, air quality, and air purification products. The company offers a range of products, including air conditioners, furnaces, heat pumps, and air purification systems, serving both residential and commercial markets. As a leading provider of climate control solutions, Lennox International plays a significant role in enhancing indoor air quality and comfort for consumers worldwide.", "EVRG": "Evergy is a public utility holding company that generates, transmits, and distributes electricity to residential, commercial, and industrial customers in Kansas and Missouri. The company's key products and services include electricity generation, transmission, and distribution, as well as natural gas distribution. As a leading provider of essential energy services, Evergy plays a critical role in powering homes, businesses, and communities across its service territories.", "SMCI": "Supermicro is a leading provider of server, storage, and networking solutions for the cloud, datacenter, artificial intelligence, and edge computing markets. The company offers a wide range of products, including motherboards, servers, storage systems, and networking equipment, designed to support high-density, high-performance computing applications. As a key supplier to major cloud and datacenter operators, Supermicro plays a critical role in enabling the growth and development of the global digital infrastructure.", "PTC": "PTC Inc. is a global provider of product lifecycle management (PLM), computer-aided design (CAD), and Internet of Things (IoT) solutions. The company offers a range of software products, including Creo, Windchill, and ThingWorx, which enable customers to design, develop, and operate complex products. By providing innovative technology solutions, PTC helps businesses improve product development, quality, and operational efficiency, driving innovation and growth in various industries.", "MKC": "McCormick & Company is a global leader in the manufacture, marketing, and distribution of spices, seasonings, and condiments, offering a wide range of products including spices, baking supplies, and specialty foods. The company's portfolio includes well-known brands such as McCormick, French's, and Old Bay, among others. As a leading player in the consumer staples industry, McCormick & Company provides essential ingredients to households and foodservice operators worldwide, driving flavor and convenience in everyday meals.", "LNT": "Alliant Energy is a utility holding company that generates, transmits, and distributes electricity and natural gas to residential, commercial, and industrial customers in the Midwest. The company operates through two primary segments: electric and gas, providing a range of products and services including electricity generation, transmission, and distribution, as well as natural gas distribution. As a major energy provider in the region, Alliant Energy plays a critical role in meeting the energy needs of its customers and communities.", "CSGP": "CoStar Group is a leading provider of commercial real estate information, analytics, and online marketplaces, offering a suite of products and services that enable clients to make informed property investment and leasing decisions. Its flagship platform, CoStar, provides access to a vast database of commercial properties, as well as market analytics and insights. By providing critical data and tools to the commercial real estate industry, CoStar Group helps facilitate more efficient and informed property transactions, driving growth and transparency in the market.", "LYB": "LyondellBasell Industries N.V. is a multinational chemical company that produces a wide range of products including polyethylene, polypropylene, and propylene oxide, which are used in various industries such as packaging, construction, and automotive. The company's products are used in the production of plastics, fibers, and other materials that are essential for modern life. As a leading producer of petrochemicals and polymers, LyondellBasell plays a critical role in meeting the growing demand for sustainable and innovative materials.", "FTV": "Fortive is a diversified industrial technology company that designs, manufactures, and markets professional and industrial products and services. Its portfolio includes brands such as Altra Industrial Motion, Brooks Automation, and Stryker Instruments, among others, offering solutions in motion control, automation, and life sciences. Fortive's products and services enable customers to improve productivity, efficiency, and safety in various industries, driving growth and innovation across the global economy.", "TKO": "TKO Group Holdings is a global provider of digital media and marketing solutions, offering a range of products and services including digital media buying, programmatic advertising, and data analytics. The company's key products and services enable businesses to reach and engage their target audiences across various digital platforms. As a leading player in the digital media landscape, TKO Group Holdings plays a significant role in shaping the way brands interact with their customers online.", "BALL": "Ball Corporation is a leading global supplier of innovative, sustainable aluminum packaging solutions for beverages, food, and household products. The company produces a wide range of products, including aluminum cans, bottles, and cups, as well as aerospace and other technologies. As a leading provider of sustainable packaging solutions, Ball Corporation plays a critical role in reducing waste and promoting environmental sustainability in the packaging industry.", "WST": "West Pharmaceutical Services is a global company that designs, manufactures, and supplies innovative, high-quality injectable solutions and other pharmaceutical packaging systems. Its key products include syringe systems, cartridges, and vials, as well as contract manufacturing and testing services for the pharmaceutical and healthcare industries. As a leading provider of critical components and services, West Pharmaceutical Services plays a vital role in ensuring the safe and efficient delivery of life-saving medications.", "WY": "Weyerhaeuser is a leading timber, land, and forest products company that operates in the United States, Canada, and other countries. The company's key products include lumber, oriented strand board (OSB), engineered wood products, and pulp. As one of the largest forestland owners in the United States, Weyerhaeuser plays a significant role in the global supply chain for wood products and sustainable forest management.", "HII": "Huntington Ingalls Industries is a leading American shipbuilding company that designs, builds, and maintains nuclear-powered aircraft carriers and submarines for the U.S. Navy, as well as commercial and government ships. The company's key products include nuclear-powered aircraft carriers, submarines, and other defense-related vessels, as well as non-nuclear ships and offshore energy facilities. As a major defense contractor, Huntington Ingalls Industries plays a critical role in supporting the U.S. military's national security and defense capabilities.", "ESS": "Essex Property Trust is a real estate investment trust (REIT) that owns, operates, and manages multifamily residential properties, primarily in the western United States. The company's portfolio consists of over 250 apartment communities with approximately 60,000 units, offering a range of amenities and services to its residents. As a leading multifamily REIT, Essex Property Trust provides a stable source of rental income and a platform for long-term growth in the residential real estate market.", "HPQ": "HP Inc. is a multinational information technology company that designs, develops, and supplies personal computers, printers, and related supplies. The company's product portfolio includes desktop and laptop computers, printers, and 3D printing solutions, catering to individual and business customers. As a leading provider of technology solutions, HP Inc. plays a significant role in shaping the digital landscape and driving innovation in the global technology industry.", "PODD": "Insulet Corporation is a medical technology company that designs, manufactures, and markets insulin pump systems for people with diabetes. The company's flagship product, the OmniPod, is a tubeless, waterproof insulin pump that provides users with greater flexibility and ease of use. By offering innovative and user-friendly solutions, Insulet helps improve the lives of people with diabetes, enabling them to better manage their condition and achieve better health outcomes.", "TXT": "Textron Inc is a multi-industry company that designs, manufactures, and delivers advanced technologies, products, and services to the aerospace and defense, industrial, and finance sectors. The company offers a range of products and services including aircraft, helicopters, unmanned aerial vehicles, and industrial equipment, as well as financing solutions. Textron's diverse portfolio enables it to provide innovative solutions to various industries, driving growth and profitability.", "VTRS": "Viatris is a global healthcare company that develops, manufactures, and markets a diverse portfolio of prescription products, including generic and branded medicines, vaccines, and over-the-counter (OTC) products. The company's product lineup includes a range of therapeutic areas, including cardiovascular, infectious diseases, and oncology, among others. As a leading player in the generic and biosimilar markets, Viatris plays a critical role in increasing access to affordable medicines globally.", "HOLX": "Hologic is a medical technology company that develops, manufactures, and supplies diagnostic and medical imaging systems, as well as surgical and molecular diagnostic products. The company's key products include breast health and cervical cancer screening systems, molecular diagnostic instruments, and surgical products for gynecologic and urogynecologic procedures. By providing innovative solutions for women's health and cancer diagnosis, Hologic plays a crucial role in improving patient outcomes and advancing healthcare.", "DECK": "Deckers Brands is a global designer, marketer, and distributor of innovative footwear and accessories. The company's portfolio includes the UGG, Koolaburra, Hoka One One, Teva, and Sanuk brands, offering a range of products from casual and performance footwear to sandals and boots. As a leading player in the premium casual footwear market, Deckers Brands matters to consumers seeking high-quality, comfortable, and stylish products.", "COO": "The Cooper Companies, Inc. is a global medical device company that designs, manufactures, and markets a range of contact lenses and eye care products, including intraocular lenses and surgical instruments. The company's key products include soft contact lenses, rigid gas permeable contact lenses, and intraocular lenses used in cataract surgery. As a leading provider of eye care solutions, Cooper Companies plays a critical role in improving vision and enhancing the quality of life for patients worldwide.", "J": "Jacobs Solutions is a global provider of technical, professional, and scientific services, delivering solutions to a diverse range of industries including aerospace, defense, healthcare, and energy. The company offers a wide range of services including engineering, project management, and operations and maintenance, as well as cybersecurity and digital transformation solutions. By providing expertise and innovative solutions, Jacobs Solutions helps clients manage complex projects and improve operational efficiency, driving growth and innovation in various sectors.", "GPC": "Genuine Parts Company is a leading global distributor of automotive replacement parts, industrial replacement parts, and business-to-business products. The company operates through its NAPA Auto Parts, Alltruck Parts, and Motion Industries brands, offering a wide range of products and services to customers in the automotive, industrial, and commercial sectors. As a major player in the automotive and industrial distribution space, Genuine Parts Company plays a vital role in supporting the maintenance and repair needs of businesses and individuals worldwide.", "NDSN": "Nordson Corporation is a leading global provider of precision engineered solutions used in the dispensing, processing, and testing of fluids, materials, and other products. The company's products and systems are used in a variety of industries, including aerospace, automotive, medical device, and consumer electronics, to name a few. Nordson's innovative solutions enable customers to improve product quality, reduce costs, and increase efficiency, driving growth and competitiveness in their respective markets.", "INVH": "Invitation Homes is a real estate investment trust that acquires, renovates, and manages single-family rental properties in the United States. The company's portfolio consists of over 80,000 properties across 16 markets, offering a range of rental homes to tenants. By providing a stable and secure housing option, Invitation Homes plays a significant role in addressing the nation's affordable housing shortage.", "MAA": "Mid-America Apartment Communities is a multifamily real estate investment trust (REIT) that owns and operates apartment communities across the United States. The company's portfolio consists of approximately 100,000 apartment homes across 14 states, offering residents a range of amenities and services. As a leading owner and operator of apartment communities, Mid-America Apartment Communities provides a vital component of the housing market, offering a stable source of income for investors and a home for thousands of residents.", "KIM": "Kimco Realty is a real estate investment trust (REIT) that owns and operates a portfolio of shopping centers and mixed-use properties across the United States. The company's key products and services include property management, leasing, and development of retail and mixed-use properties, with a focus on creating vibrant community spaces. As one of the largest publicly traded REITs in the US, Kimco Realty plays a significant role in shaping the retail landscape and supporting local economies.", "PNR": "Pentair is a global industrial company that designs, manufactures, and markets industrial and commercial water treatment and flow control solutions, as well as valves and controls. The company's key products and services include residential and commercial pool equipment, water filtration systems, and valves and controls for various industries. By providing innovative solutions for water management and flow control, Pentair plays a critical role in supporting global water conservation and infrastructure development.", "IEX": "IDEX Corporation is a leading global provider of pumps, valves, and other fluid-handling equipment and engineered solutions for various industries, including food and beverage, chemical, and pharmaceutical. The company's product portfolio includes brands such as Almatec, Gorman-Rupp, and IDEX Flowtronics, among others. As a key supplier to various manufacturing sectors, IDEX plays a vital role in ensuring the efficient production and processing of goods.", "TRMB": "Trimble Inc. is a technology company that provides solutions in positioning, mobility, and connectivity for the global construction, agriculture, and transportation industries. The company's key products and services include geospatial and navigation software, mapping and surveying solutions, and Internet of Things (IoT) technology. Trimble's innovative solutions enable businesses to improve productivity, reduce costs, and enhance decision-making, driving growth and efficiency across various sectors.", "CDW": "CDW Corporation is a leading multi-brand provider of information technology solutions to business, government, education, and healthcare customers through its network of over 250 locations and online presence. The company offers a wide range of products and services, including hardware, software, and services, from top technology brands. By providing a one-stop-shop for IT solutions, CDW enables its customers to simplify their technology procurement and management processes, improving their overall efficiency and productivity.", "FFIV": "F5, Inc. is a global leader in multi-cloud application services, providing solutions that enable secure, fast, and scalable delivery of applications and services. The company's key products and services include application delivery controllers, traffic management, security, and analytics solutions, as well as cloud and hybrid infrastructure solutions. F5's technology helps organizations improve the performance, security, and availability of their applications and services, driving business success in today's digital economy.", "APTV": "Aptiv is a global technology company that designs, manufactures, and supplies automotive electrical, electronic, and safety systems to original equipment manufacturers. The company's key products and services include vehicle electrification, autonomous driving, and advanced driver-assistance systems. As a leading supplier to the automotive industry, Aptiv plays a critical role in enabling the development of safer, more connected, and more sustainable vehicles.", "CLX": "Clorox is a multinational consumer goods company that manufactures and markets a range of household, consumer, and professional products, including cleaning supplies, household chemicals, and food products. Key brands include Clorox bleach, Glad trash bags, and Burt's Bees natural personal care products. As a leading player in the consumer staples sector, Clorox provides essential products for households and businesses worldwide.", "TYL": "Tyler Technologies is a provider of integrated software and technology services focused on the public sector, offering a range of products and services that support the administrative, financial, and operational needs of local governments, schools, and other public entities. The company's key offerings include municipal and county software solutions, court case management, and public safety software, among others. By streamlining processes and improving efficiency, Tyler Technologies helps public sector organizations enhance citizen engagement, reduce costs, and improve overall service delivery.", "AVY": "Avery Dennison Corporation is a global materials science and manufacturing company that designs, manufactures, and markets a range of products and solutions for various industries, including labeling and packaging, materials science, and retail branding. The company's key products and services include pressure-sensitive materials, RFID inlays, and digital printing solutions, among others. Avery Dennison's innovative materials and technologies enable businesses to enhance their brand experiences, improve operational efficiency, and drive sustainability.", "REG": "Regency Centers is a real estate investment trust (REIT) that owns, operates, and develops high-quality, shopping centers in the United States. The company's portfolio consists of grocery-anchored and community shopping centers that provide a convenient and accessible retail experience for customers. By offering a platform for retailers to connect with consumers, Regency Centers plays a vital role in supporting local economies and driving economic growth.", "NWS": "News Corp (Class B) is a global media and information services company that provides news, information, and content through a diverse portfolio of businesses, including news and media outlets, book publishing, and digital real estate services. The company's key products and services include The Wall Street Journal, New York Post, HarperCollins Publishers, and REA Group. As a leading player in the global media landscape, News Corp plays a significant role in shaping public discourse and providing essential information to consumers worldwide.", "PSKY": "Paramount Skydance Corporation is a leading media and entertainment company that operates through a portfolio of film and television production studios, including Paramount Pictures and Skydance Media. The company develops, produces, and distributes a range of content across various platforms, including film, television, and digital media, offering a diverse slate of entertainment options to global audiences. As a major player in the entertainment industry, Paramount Skydance Corporation plays a significant role in shaping popular culture and driving economic growth through its creative and innovative storytelling.", "MAS": "Masco Corporation is a leading manufacturer of home improvement and building products, offering a diverse portfolio of branded and private-label products, including faucets, cabinets, and doors. The company's products cater to the needs of homeowners, builders, and professionals in the construction industry, driving growth and innovation in the home improvement market. As a key player in the industry, Masco's products and solutions enhance the quality and functionality of homes and buildings, contributing to the company's position as a leading global manufacturer.", "EG": "Everest Group is a global research and consulting firm that provides insights and solutions to help organizations optimize their operations, improve performance, and make informed decisions. The company offers a range of services, including research reports, consulting, and training, to clients across various industries. By providing data-driven insights and strategic guidance, Everest Group helps organizations navigate complex business challenges and achieve their goals.", "AKAM": "Akamai Technologies is a global leader in content delivery network (CDN) services, cloud security, and edge computing solutions. The company's products and services enable businesses to deliver, optimize, and secure online content, applications, and experiences across the globe. By providing a high-performance edge platform, Akamai helps organizations improve user experiences, reduce latency, and enhance security in the digital age.", "BEN": "Franklin Resources is a global investment management company that provides a range of investment products and services to individual investors, financial institutions, and institutional clients. The company's key products include mutual funds, exchange-traded funds, and other investment vehicles that offer a variety of asset management strategies. As one of the largest asset managers in the world, Franklin Resources plays a significant role in shaping the global investment landscape.", "UDR": "UDR, Inc. is a real estate investment trust (REIT) that owns, acquires, renovates, develops, and manages multifamily apartment communities primarily in the United States. The company's key products and services include the ownership and operation of over 130 properties containing more than 58,000 apartments across 26 states and the Washington, D.C. metropolitan area. UDR's business model provides a stable source of income for investors through rental income and property appreciation.", "NWSA": "News Corp (Class A) is a global media and information services company that operates in the areas of news and information, book publishing, digital real estate services, and cable network programming. The company's key products and services include The Wall Street Journal, HarperCollins Publishers, and Foxtel, a pay-television service in Australia. As a leading global media company, News Corp plays a significant role in shaping public discourse and providing access to information and entertainment.", "ERIE": "Erie Indemnity is a financial services holding company that provides underwriting, risk management, and other insurance-related services to the Erie Insurance Group. The company offers a range of products, including property and casualty insurance, workers' compensation insurance, and specialty insurance products. As a key partner to Erie Insurance Group, Erie Indemnity plays a vital role in supporting the growth and operations of one of the largest property and casualty insurance groups in the United States.", "GEN": "Gen Digital is a global consumer software company that provides digital safety and security solutions to individuals and families. The company's key products and services include Norton antivirus software, LifeLock identity theft protection, and other digital security offerings. By protecting consumers from online threats, Gen Digital plays a critical role in maintaining the integrity of the digital ecosystem and safeguarding personal data.", "ALLE": "Allegion is a global security products and solutions provider that offers a range of door and access control systems, electronic locks, and other security-related products and services. The company's products are used in various settings, including commercial, institutional, and residential properties, to enhance safety, security, and convenience. Allegion's solutions help protect people, places, and assets, supporting the growth and development of its customers and the communities they serve.", "HRL": "Hormel Foods is a multinational consumer goods company that develops, manufactures, and markets a range of branded food products, including meat, poultry, and processed foods such as SPAM, Skippy peanut butter, and Hormel bacon. The company's portfolio of brands caters to various consumer needs, from convenience foods to natural and organic products. As a leading player in the global packaged food industry, Hormel Foods plays a significant role in meeting the evolving demands of consumers worldwide.", "HAS": "Hasbro, Inc. is a global play and entertainment company that designs, produces, and markets a range of toys, games, and consumer products, including iconic brands such as Monopoly, Play-Doh, and Nerf. The company's portfolio also includes entertainment franchises like Magic: The Gathering and Dungeons & Dragons, as well as partnerships with popular franchises like Marvel and Star Wars. As a leading player in the global toy and game industry, Hasbro's products bring joy and imagination to children and adults worldwide.", "HST": "Host Hotels & Resorts is a lodging real estate investment trust (REIT) that owns and operates upscale and luxury hotels in the United States, Europe, and Asia. The company's portfolio includes over 130 properties with more than 59,000 rooms, primarily under management agreements with leading hotel brands. As a major player in the hospitality industry, Host Hotels & Resorts provides investors with a diversified portfolio of high-end hotels, generating stable cash flows and long-term growth potential.", "ALGN": "Align Technology is a medical device company that designs, manufactures, and markets a range of dental and orthodontic products, including the Invisalign clear aligner system and iTero intraoral scanners. These products enable orthodontists, dentists, and other healthcare professionals to provide patients with more efficient, effective, and aesthetically pleasing orthodontic and restorative treatments. By expanding access to high-quality orthodontic care, Align Technology is helping to transform the dental and orthodontic industries.", "DPZ": "Domino's Pizza, Inc. is a leading global pizza delivery company that operates a network of company-owned and franchise-owned stores. The company offers a variety of pizzas, sides, and desserts through its online ordering platform, mobile app, and in-store locations, catering to changing consumer preferences for convenience and digital ordering. As a prominent player in the quick-service restaurant industry, Domino's matters for its significant market share and influence on the consumer discretionary sector.", "BF.B": "Brown-Forman Corporation is a leading American spirits and wine company that manufactures and markets a wide range of beverage products globally. Its portfolio includes iconic brands such as Jack Daniel's Tennessee Whiskey, Woodford Reserve, Old Forester, and Finlandia Vodka, among others. As a major player in the spirits industry, Brown-Forman's products are widely available in over 170 countries, making it a significant contributor to the global beverage market.", "GNRC": "Generac Holdings Inc designs, manufactures, and sells power generation equipment and other power products for residential, commercial, industrial, and construction markets. The company's product portfolio includes portable and standby generators, home standby power systems, and other power solutions. As a leading provider of backup power systems, Generac plays a critical role in ensuring the reliability and resilience of critical infrastructure and emergency services.", "BBY": "Best Buy Co., Inc. operates as a leading multi-channel retailer of technology products and services in the United States, Canada, and Mexico. The company offers a wide range of products, including consumer electronics, home office products, appliances, and entertainment products, as well as services such as installation, maintenance, and repair. As a major player in the consumer electronics retail market, Best Buy provides customers with a one-stop shopping experience for their technology needs.", "UHS": "Universal Health Services operates a network of acute care hospitals, behavioral health and addiction treatment facilities, and ambulatory surgery centers across the United States. The company provides a range of healthcare services, including inpatient and outpatient treatment for mental health and substance abuse disorders, as well as surgical services and emergency care. As a leading provider of behavioral health services, Universal Health Services plays a critical role in addressing the growing need for mental health and addiction treatment in the US.", "SWK": "Stanley Black & Decker is a leading global provider of tools and storage, security, and engineered fastening systems. The company offers a diverse portfolio of iconic brands, including Stanley, Black+Decker, DeWalt, and Facom, among others, which cater to professionals and DIYers in the construction, automotive, and industrial sectors. As a key player in the global industrial market, Stanley Black & Decker's innovative products and solutions drive productivity, efficiency, and safety in various industries.", "SOLV": "Solventum is a leading developer of innovative medical diagnostic technologies, specializing in the design and manufacturing of laboratory equipment and reagents for the detection of infectious diseases. The company's flagship products include the Solventum Analyzer, a high-performance instrument used to detect and quantify various biomarkers, and its line of proprietary reagents, which enhance the accuracy and efficiency of diagnostic testing. By providing critical tools for disease diagnosis and surveillance, Solventum plays a vital role in public health efforts worldwide.", "DOC": "Healthpeak Properties is a real estate investment trust (REIT) that invests in and manages a diversified portfolio of healthcare properties, including medical offices, outpatient facilities, and senior living communities. The company's properties are primarily leased to healthcare providers and operators, generating rental income and providing a stable source of returns for investors. As a leading healthcare-focused REIT, Healthpeak Properties plays a critical role in supporting the delivery of healthcare services and providing a platform for investors to participate in the growing demand for healthcare real estate.", "SJM": "The J.M. Smucker Company is a leading manufacturer and marketer of consumer food and beverage products, offering a diverse portfolio of brands including Folgers coffee, Jif peanut butter, and Smucker's fruit spreads. The company's products are sold in the United States, Canada, and internationally, catering to a wide range of consumer preferences and needs. As a prominent player in the consumer staples sector, The J.M. Smucker Company provides essential food and beverage products to households and businesses worldwide.", "GDDY": "GoDaddy Inc is a technology company providing cloud-based products and services to small businesses, web designers, and individuals. Its key offerings include domain name registration, website hosting, and security solutions, as well as e-commerce platforms and digital marketing tools. As a leading provider of online presence solutions, GoDaddy enables businesses to establish a professional online presence and reach their target audiences.", "PNW": "Pinnacle West Capital Corporation is a holding company that primarily operates through its principal subsidiary, Arizona Public Service Company (APS), a vertically integrated electric utility company that generates, transmits, and distributes electricity to retail customers in Arizona. APS provides electricity to approximately 1.3 million retail customers through a diverse mix of coal, nuclear, natural gas, and renewable energy sources. As a leading utility company in the southwestern United States, Pinnacle West plays a critical role in meeting the region's growing energy demands.", "GL": "Globe Life is a holding company that operates as a life and supplemental health insurance company, primarily offering individual supplemental insurance products and annuities. Its key products include life insurance, accident insurance, and fixed annuities, which provide financial protection and savings solutions to policyholders. As a leading provider of supplemental insurance, Globe Life plays a significant role in helping individuals and families manage financial risks and achieve long-term financial security.", "JKHY": "Jack Henry & Associates is a financial technology company that provides integrated technology solutions to community and regional banks, credit unions, and other financial institutions. The company's key products and services include core banking systems, payments processing, and digital banking solutions. By enabling financial institutions to streamline operations and enhance customer experiences, Jack Henry & Associates helps to promote financial inclusion and stability.", "TTD": "The Trade Desk is a global technology company that provides a self-service, cloud-based platform for data consumers to buy and sell data-driven advertising. The company's platform, known as the Trade Desk, offers a range of products and services, including data management, ad serving, and attribution analytics, allowing advertisers to target and measure their campaigns across various digital channels. By providing a more efficient and effective way to buy and sell data-driven advertising, The Trade Desk has become a key player in the digital advertising ecosystem.", "AIZ": "Assurant is a global provider of risk management products and services, offering a range of insurance, warranty, and other related products to consumers and businesses. The company's key products and services include property and casualty insurance, vehicle protection, and extended service contracts, among others. By providing these solutions, Assurant helps individuals and businesses manage risk and protect their assets, making it a significant player in the financial services industry.", "IVZ": "Invesco is a global investment manager that offers a range of financial products and services, including actively managed mutual funds, exchange-traded funds (ETFs), and institutional investment solutions. The company provides investment products across various asset classes, including equities, fixed income, and alternative investments, catering to individual and institutional investors. As one of the largest investment managers in the world, Invesco plays a significant role in shaping the global investment landscape.", "CPT": "Camden Property Trust is a multifamily real estate investment trust (REIT) that owns, manages, and develops apartment communities across the United States. The company's portfolio consists of over 250 properties with more than 140,000 apartment homes, offering a range of living options to residents. As a leading owner and operator of multifamily properties, Camden Property Trust provides a stable source of income and long-term growth for investors.", "IT": "Gartner is a global research and advisory company that provides information technology (IT) research and analysis to business leaders, IT professionals, and technology companies. The company offers a range of products and services, including research reports, advisory services, and conferences, to help clients navigate complex IT landscapes and make informed decisions. By providing objective and actionable insights, Gartner helps organizations optimize their IT strategies and stay ahead of the competition in a rapidly evolving technology landscape.", "APA": "APA Corporation is an independent oil and natural gas exploration and production company that operates onshore and offshore assets in the United States, Egypt, and the United Kingdom. The company's key products include crude oil, natural gas liquids, and natural gas, with a focus on developing and producing these resources in a safe and environmentally responsible manner. As a leading energy producer, APA Corporation plays a significant role in meeting global energy demand while navigating the transition to a lower-carbon future.", "ZBRA": "Zebra Technologies is a global leader in enterprise asset tracking and automated identification solutions, offering a range of products and services that enable businesses to track, manage, and optimize their operations. The company's portfolio includes barcode scanners, printers, mobile computers, and software solutions that facilitate inventory management, supply chain visibility, and data analytics. By providing innovative technology solutions, Zebra Technologies helps organizations improve efficiency, reduce costs, and enhance customer experiences.", "BLDR": "Builders FirstSource is a leading supplier of building materials, manufactured products, and value-added services to professional builders, including single-family and multi-family residential and light commercial markets. The company offers a range of products, including lumber, roofing, siding, drywall, millwork, doors, and windows, as well as value-added services such as installation and design assistance. As a key supplier to the residential and light commercial construction industry, Builders FirstSource plays a critical role in meeting the growing demand for housing and commercial construction.", "WYNN": "Wynn Resorts is a global leader in the hospitality and gaming industry, operating luxury resorts and casinos in the United States, Macau, and Las Vegas. The company's key products and services include upscale hotels, gaming facilities, and entertainment options. As a major player in the gaming and hospitality sector, Wynn Resorts provides a unique blend of luxury and entertainment, catering to high-end customers and generating significant revenue.", "RVTY": "Revvity is a healthcare company that develops and commercializes digital therapeutics for chronic diseases, focusing on mental health and wellness. The company offers a range of products and services, including its flagship digital therapeutic, Revvity's flagship product, which provides personalized mental health support. By leveraging technology to improve patient outcomes, Revvity aims to revolutionize the treatment of mental health conditions and improve the quality of life for millions of people worldwide.", "AOS": "A. O. Smith is a leading global manufacturer of water heaters and boilers, as well as a provider of water treatment and water filtration solutions. The company's products cater to residential, commercial, and industrial markets, with a focus on energy efficiency and sustainability. A. O. Smith's offerings enable customers to conserve water and reduce energy consumption, making it a significant player in the water treatment and heating industry.", "DVA": "DaVita Inc is a leading provider of kidney care services and products in the United States, offering dialysis and transplantation services to patients with chronic kidney disease. The company operates a network of freestanding dialysis centers, acute hospital services, and affiliated physician practices, providing care to approximately 210,000 patients. DaVita's services and products help patients with end-stage renal disease (ESRD) manage their condition and improve their quality of life.", "NCLH": "Norwegian Cruise Line Holdings is a global cruise and vacation company that operates a diverse fleet of cruise ships, offering a range of onboard amenities and itineraries to destinations worldwide. The company's key products and services include cruises, land and sea vacations, and other travel-related offerings through its three brands: Norwegian Cruise Line, Oceania Cruises, and Regent Seven Seas Cruises. As a leading player in the cruise industry, Norwegian Cruise Line Holdings provides unique travel experiences to millions of passengers annually, generating significant revenue and economic impact.", "BXP": "BXP, Inc., a member of the S&P 500, is a real estate investment trust (REIT) that owns and operates Class A office properties primarily in the United States. The company's portfolio includes high-quality office buildings in major markets such as Boston, New York City, and Washington, D.C. BXP's properties provide a platform for businesses to house their operations, driving economic growth and innovation in the regions they serve.", "BAX": "Baxter International is a multinational healthcare company that develops, manufactures, and markets medical devices, pharmaceuticals, and biotechnology products. The company's key products include intravenous solutions, infusion systems, and renal therapy products, as well as sterile injectables and biosurgery products. Baxter plays a critical role in the healthcare industry by providing life-sustaining therapies and medical products to patients worldwide.", "HSIC": "Henry Schein is a healthcare solutions company that provides products and services to office-based dental and medical professionals, as well as animal health customers. The company offers a range of products, including dental equipment, medical equipment, and pharmaceuticals, as well as practice management software and other business solutions. By helping healthcare professionals deliver quality patient care, Henry Schein plays a critical role in improving health outcomes and advancing the healthcare industry.", "TAP": "Molson Coors Beverage Company is a leading brewer and beverage company that produces a portfolio of iconic brands, including Coors, Miller Lite, and Blue Moon, as well as other beers, hard seltzers, and non-alcoholic beverages. The company operates in the United States, Canada, Europe, and other international markets, offering a diverse range of products to consumers. As a major player in the global beverage industry, Molson Coors Beverage Company plays a significant role in shaping consumer preferences and trends.", "MGM": "MGM Resorts International is a leading global hospitality and entertainment company that operates a diverse portfolio of resorts, casinos, and entertainment venues across the United States and internationally. The company's key products and services include gaming, hotel accommodations, dining, entertainment, and leisure activities. As a major player in the gaming and hospitality industry, MGM Resorts is a significant contributor to the global economy and a popular destination for leisure and business travelers.", "FRT": "Federal Realty Investment Trust is a real estate investment trust that owns and operates a diversified portfolio of retail and mixed-use properties across the United States. The company's portfolio includes high-quality shopping centers, restaurants, and entertainment venues, as well as office and residential properties. By providing a unique blend of retail, dining, and entertainment options, Federal Realty aims to create vibrant community hubs that drive economic growth and enhance the quality of life for its customers and tenants.", "ARE": "Alexandria Real Estate Equities is a real estate investment trust (REIT) that owns, operates, and develops life science and technology campuses primarily on the West Coast of the United States. The company focuses on providing high-quality, specialized properties to pharmaceutical, biotechnology, and life science companies, as well as technology and biotechnology research institutions. By offering customized facilities and amenities, Alexandria Real Estate Equities enables its tenants to advance their research and development efforts, driving innovation and growth in the life science and technology sectors.", "CAG": "Conagra Brands is a leading food company that produces a diverse portfolio of packaged food products for retail and foodservice customers. The company's key brands include Healthy Choice, Marie's, Reddi-wip, and Orville Redenbacher's, among others, offering a range of frozen, canned, and ready-to-eat meals, snacks, and condiments. As a major player in the consumer staples sector, Conagra Brands provides essential food products to households and businesses worldwide.", "TECH": "Bio-Techne Corporation is a global life sciences company that develops, manufactures, and markets a range of biotechnology products and reagents used in research, diagnostics, and bioproduction. The company's key products include cytokines, growth factors, and other biochemical reagents, as well as instruments and consumables for life sciences research and diagnostics. Bio-Techne's products play a critical role in advancing medical research, diagnostics, and biotechnology applications, enabling scientists and researchers to better understand and combat diseases.", "MOS": "The Mosaic Company is a leading producer and marketer of concentrated phosphate and potash crop nutrients, serving the global agricultural industry. The company's key products include phosphate-based fertilizers, potash fertilizers, and other nutrient solutions that help farmers increase crop yields and improve food security. As a critical supplier of essential nutrients, Mosaic plays a vital role in meeting the world's growing demand for food and other agricultural products.", "CRL": "Charles River Laboratories International, Inc. is a global contract research organization that provides a range of services and products to support the discovery, development, and commercialization of pharmaceuticals, biotechnology, and medical devices. The company offers laboratory testing and research model services, as well as discovery and safety assessment services for preclinical and clinical research. By providing high-quality research and testing services, Charles River Laboratories enables the development of life-saving treatments and therapies.", "SWKS": "Skyworks Solutions is a leading global provider of analog and mixed-signal semiconductors, offering a portfolio of solutions that enable connectivity, mobility, and power management in a wide range of applications, including smartphones, tablets, and automotive systems. The company's products include amplifiers, attenuators, and switches, as well as power management and RF solutions. As a key supplier to major technology companies, Skyworks plays a critical role in the development of next-generation wireless and automotive technologies.", "FDS": "FactSet is a global provider of financial data and analytics, offering a range of products and services that help investment professionals make informed decisions. Its key offerings include financial data and research, portfolio analysis and risk management tools, and cloud-based solutions for investment operations. By providing accurate and timely financial information, FactSet enables investors to optimize their portfolios and make more informed investment decisions.", "POOL": "Pool Corporation is a leading wholesale distributor of swimming pool and related equipment, providing products and services to the pool and spa industry. The company offers a wide range of products, including pool equipment, chemicals, and accessories, as well as installation and maintenance services. As a key supplier to the industry, Pool Corporation plays a significant role in the growth and development of the pool and spa market.", "EPAM": "EPAM Systems is a leading global provider of digital platform engineering and software development services, helping clients navigate the digital transformation of their businesses. The company offers a range of services including cloud infrastructure, artificial intelligence, data analytics, and cybersecurity, among others. As a key player in the digital transformation space, EPAM enables clients to innovate and stay competitive in a rapidly changing market.", "CPB": "Campbell's Company is a leading manufacturer and marketer of food and beverage products, offering a diverse portfolio of brands including Campbell's soups, Prego pasta sauces, Swanson broths, and V8 juices. The company's products are sold in over 120 countries and are a staple in many households, providing consumers with convenient and nutritious meal solutions. As a major player in the consumer staples industry, Campbell's Company plays a significant role in meeting the evolving needs of consumers for healthy, sustainable, and convenient food options.", "MOH": "Molina Healthcare is a health insurance company that provides managed care services to low-income individuals and families through government-sponsored programs, including Medicaid and the State Children's Health Insurance Program. The company offers a range of products and services, including health insurance plans, pharmacy benefits management, and care management programs. By providing access to affordable healthcare, Molina Healthcare plays a critical role in improving the health outcomes and well-being of vulnerable populations.", "MTCH": "Match Group is a leading provider of dating products and services, offering a portfolio of brands that cater to diverse user preferences and demographics. Its key products include Tinder, Hinge, OkCupid, Plenty of Fish, and Match.com, among others, which facilitate connections and relationships through online platforms. As a major player in the online dating industry, Match Group's services enable millions of users to find meaningful relationships, making it a significant player in the Communication Services sector.", "PAYC": "Paycom Software, Inc. is a cloud-based human capital management (HCM) software provider offering a range of products and services, including payroll, time and labor management, benefits, talent management, and HR management. The company's flagship platform enables businesses to manage their workforce, automate administrative tasks, and gain insights into their operations. By streamlining HR processes and improving workforce management, Paycom helps organizations increase productivity, reduce costs, and enhance employee experiences.", "LW": "Lamb Weston Holdings, Inc., a leading global producer and marketer of frozen potato products, offers a diverse portfolio of frozen potato, sweet potato, and other vegetable products. The company's key products include frozen french fries, hash browns, and other potato specialties, serving major foodservice and retail customers worldwide. As a leading player in the frozen potato market, Lamb Weston plays a critical role in meeting the growing demand for convenient, high-quality frozen food products."};
